as a healing process.

00:01:29.855 --> 00:01:31.230 align:middle line:84%
Can you explain
a little bit more

00:01:31.230 --> 00:01:33.262 align:middle line:90%
about what you mean by that?

00:01:33.262 --> 00:01:37.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I would say this
depression is a comparison

00:01:37.410 --> 00:01:41.470 align:middle line:84%
of our current reality to
a unrealistic expectation,

00:01:41.470 --> 00:01:44.040 align:middle line:84%
fantasy, or delusion
that we're addicted to.

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:45.300 align:middle line:90%
Many people are depressed.

00:01:45.300 --> 00:01:48.435 align:middle line:84%
And when I asked them, so what
are you expecting it to be?

00:01:48.435 --> 00:01:51.080 align:middle line:84%
And they go, well, it
should be this way.

00:01:51.080 --> 00:01:53.000 align:middle line:84%
Life should be this way
or this aspect of life

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:54.260 align:middle line:90%
should be this way.

00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:56.375 align:middle line:84%
When I asked them, so
if it was that way,

00:01:56.375 --> 00:01:58.220 align:middle line:84%
what would be the
drawback to that?

00:01:58.220 --> 00:01:59.318 align:middle line:90%
They have no drawbacks.

00:01:59.318 --> 00:02:00.860 align:middle line:84%
So they have a
fantasy and a delusion

00:02:00.860 --> 00:02:03.020 align:middle line:84%
because everything in
life has two sides.

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:05.172 align:middle line:84%
So therefore, their
reality is unfulfilling

00:02:05.172 --> 00:02:07.130 align:middle line:84%
because they're comparing
it to this thing that

00:02:07.130 --> 00:02:08.439 align:middle line:90%
has no downsides.

00:02:08.439 --> 00:02:10.550 align:middle line:84%
And so when life has
a balance, compared

00:02:10.550 --> 00:02:14.370 align:middle line:84%
to something that has no
downside, they are depressed.

00:02:14.370 --> 00:02:18.050 align:middle line:84%
So I would say depression is a
feedback mechanism to awaken us

00:02:18.050 --> 00:02:21.200 align:middle line:84%
consciously to the delusions,
and unrealistic expectations,

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.240 align:middle line:84%
and fancies that
we get addicted to,

00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:25.970 align:middle line:84%
and to give us an opportunity to
break that-- to associate pain

00:02:25.970 --> 00:02:28.700 align:middle line:84%
with that fantasy pleasure
to help us stabilize

00:02:28.700 --> 00:02:29.900 align:middle line:90%
ourselves and get in order.

00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:31.948 align:middle line:84%
But we keep having
this hedonic treadmill

00:02:31.948 --> 00:02:33.740 align:middle line:84%
and wanting to get on
one side of the world

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:35.825 align:middle line:84%
instead of embracing the
two sides of life, which

00:02:35.825 --> 00:02:36.950 align:middle line:90%
helps us stabilize ourself.

00:02:36.950 --> 00:02:38.240 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:41.340 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm seeing
there is, there

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:45.740 align:middle line:84%
is a massive lesson around
honoring the law of polarity.

00:02:45.740 --> 00:02:48.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, when we have objective
reasoning and we have a more

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:51.050 align:middle line:84%
balanced mind, we
are more stable--

00:02:51.050 --> 00:02:53.630 align:middle line:84%
when we have some sort of a
subjective bias where we're

00:02:53.630 --> 00:02:55.370 align:middle line:90%
striving for a one-sided world.

00:02:55.370 --> 00:02:57.410 align:middle line:84%
