a teaching that said,

00:02:57.410 --> 00:02:59.298 align:middle line:84%
the desire for that
which is unavailable

00:02:59.298 --> 00:03:01.340 align:middle line:84%
and the desire to avoid
that which is unavoidable

00:03:01.340 --> 00:03:03.590 align:middle line:90%
is a source of human suffering.

00:03:03.590 --> 00:03:07.190 align:middle line:84%
And many people are striving
for a one-sided world instead

00:03:07.190 --> 00:03:09.373 align:middle line:84%
of embracing the two sides
that life has to offer.

00:03:09.373 --> 00:03:11.540 align:middle line:84%
>> And how they can actually
complement one another.

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:12.440 align:middle line:90%
>> You need both.

00:03:12.440 --> 00:03:14.180 align:middle line:84%
I asked a lady the
other day in one

00:03:14.180 --> 00:03:16.250 align:middle line:84%
of my seminars, "The
Breakthrough Experience--"

00:03:16.250 --> 00:03:18.620 align:middle line:90%
I said, if I gave you a magnet--

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:21.710 align:middle line:84%
and I said, I'm going to give
you $1 billion worth of cash

00:03:21.710 --> 00:03:23.745 align:middle line:84%
if you can give me one
pole of the magnet back.

00:03:23.745 --> 00:03:25.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to give
you the whole magnet.

00:03:25.370 --> 00:03:27.740 align:middle line:84%
Give me just the
positive pole back.

00:03:27.740 --> 00:03:31.060 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you're ignorant, you
try to cut the magnet in half

00:03:31.060 --> 00:03:31.940 align:middle line:90%
and try to get--

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:33.020 align:middle line:84%
but what happens when
you cut it in half?

00:03:33.020 --> 00:03:35.353 align:middle line:84%
You get two, little magnets
with positive and negative--

00:03:35.353 --> 00:03:37.010 align:middle line:84%
or, if you cut it
again, four magnets.

00:03:37.010 --> 00:03:39.172 align:middle line:84%
You can't really
separate the two.

00:03:39.172 --> 00:03:40.880 align:middle line:84%
And we tend to separate
the inseparables,

00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:43.520 align:middle line:84%
and divide the indivisibles, and
try to label the unlabelables,

00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:46.700 align:middle line:84%
and name the ineffables, and
polarize the unpolarizables,

00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:49.400 align:middle line:84%
and not embrace
both sides of life.

00:03:49.400 --> 00:03:52.770 align:middle line:84%
So a person striving
for a one-sided magnet

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:53.570 align:middle line:90%
will be futile.

00:03:53.570 --> 00:03:54.500 align:middle line:90%
And this is what people feel.

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:56.458 align:middle line:84%
They feel futile and
depressed because they are

00:03:56.458 --> 00:03:59.360 align:middle line:90%
striving for a one-sided world.

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:02.360 align:middle line:90%
>> So the Demartini Method--

00:04:02.360 --> 00:04:06.500 align:middle line:84%
when we're looking at overcoming
depression and anxiety as one

00:04:06.500 --> 00:04:10.430 align:middle line:84%
particular area, you have a
very simple, three-step process.

00:04:10.430 --> 00:04:12.347 align:middle line:84%
Can you share what that
three-step process is?

00:04:12.347 --> 00:04:13.147 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:13.147 --> 00:04:15.230 align:middle line:84%
What are you specifically
comparing your life to,

00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:17.750 align:middle line:84%
the way you wish it would be,
which is sort of the delusion

00:04:17.750 --> 00:04:19.100 align:middle line:90%
and fantasy?

00:04:19.100 --> 00:04:21.410 align:middle line:90%
What's the drawbacks of that?

00:04:21.410 --> 00:04:23.762 align:middle line:84%
And what's the
benefit of reality?

00:04:23.762 --> 00:04:25.970 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're comparing
yourself and your reality

00:04:25.970 --> 00:04:28.250 align:middle line:84%
to something that's not
there, there's no way

00:04:28.250 --> 00:04:29.780 align:middle line:84%
you can win because
that's not real.

00:04:29.780 --> 00:04:31.220 align:middle line:90%
What's real is what's real.

00:04:31.220 --> 00:04:34.130 align:middle line:84%
So what's the benefit
of what's real?

00:04:34.130 --> 00:04:36.665 align:middle line:84%
And what's the drawback of the
fantasy you wish it would be?

00:04:36.665 --> 00:04:38.540 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes, you
can hold onto the idea

00:04:38.540 --> 00:04:40.290 align:middle line:84%
that thing is supposed
to be a certain way

00:04:40.290 --> 00:04:42.770 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to be all
peachy keen when it's that way.

00:04:42.770 --> 00:04:44.460 align:middle line:90%
I have to share a story.

00:04:44.460 --> 00:04:46.820 align:middle line:84%
I had a gentleman that
was bitter and really

00:04:46.820 --> 00:04:50.210 align:middle line:84%
resentful to his father, and
depressed because his father

00:04:50.210 --> 00:04:52.010 align:middle line:90%
never showed affection for him.

00:04:52.010 --> 00:04:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him a simple
question in "The Breakthrough

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:57.980 align:middle line:84%
Experience--" so if your father
had done that in your life

00:04:57.980 --> 00:05:00.190 align:middle line:84%
when you were 16,
before you left home

00:05:00.190 --> 00:05:01.197 align:middle line:90%
when he kicked you out--

00:05:01.197 --> 00:05:03.530 align:middle line:84%
if he had been this affectionate
person like you wanted,

00:05:03.530 --> 00:05:04.380 align:middle line:90%
what would've been the drawback?

00:05:04.380 --> 00:05:05.880 align:middle line:84%
He goes, there would
be no drawback.

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:07.030 align:middle line:90%
I'd have been happy.

00:05:07.030 --> 00:05:07.830 align:middle line:90%
And I said, no.

00:05:07.830 --> 00:05:09.080 align:middle line:90%
What would be the drawback?

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:10.460 align:middle line:90%
He goes, I can't see any.

00:05:10.460 --> 00:05:11.990 align:middle line:84%
I said, did you have any
brothers and sisters?

00:05:11.990 --> 00:05:12.830 align:middle line:90%
He goes, well, yeah.

00:05:12.830 --> 00:05:13.850 align:middle line:90%
I had a brother.

00:05:13.850 --> 00:05:15.433 align:middle line:84%
And did your father
give the affection

00:05:15.433 --> 00:05:17.690 align:middle line:84%
that you wished that you'd
gotten to the brother?

00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:18.490 align:middle line:90%
He said, yeah.

00:05:18.490 --> 00:05:19.873 align:middle line:90%
He got all the affection.

00:05:19.873 --> 00:05:21.790 align:middle line:84%
I said, would you trade
places with him today?

00:05:21.790 --> 00:05:22.400 align:middle line:90%
He goes, no.

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:23.270 align:middle line:90%
He's still living at home.

00:05:23.270 --> 00:05:23.960 align:middle line:90%
He's never growing up.

00:05:23.960 --> 00:05:25.710 align:middle line:84%
He's never even gone on
his own and has a job,

00:05:25.710 --> 00:05:27.377 align:middle line:84%
but he's waiting for
the parents to die.

00:05:27.377 --> 00:05:30.778 align:middle line:84%
He's basically dependent,
an enabled disabled person.

00:05:30.778 --> 00:05:32.570 align:middle line:84%
I said, so you'd rather
have had that life?

00:05:32.570 --> 00:05:34.460 align:middle line:84%
He goes, I would
have until I just

00:05:34.460 --> 00:05:36.290 align:middle line:90%
realized what you just said.

00:05:36.290 --> 00:05:38.900 align:middle line:84%
I said, so what you got is
your father believed in you,

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:40.503 align:middle line:84%
and challenged
you, and said, go.

00:05:40.503 --> 00:05:41.420 align:middle line:90%
You stand on your own.

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:42.530 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't have done
that if he didn't believe

00:05:42.530 --> 00:05:43.693 align:middle line:90%
you could do it.

00:05:43.693 --> 00:05:45.110 align:middle line:84%
And you're an
entrepreneur today--

00:05:45.110 --> 00:05:46.420 align:middle line:90%
a very successful entrepreneur.

00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:49.340 align:middle line:84%
And your brother, who you
thought you wanted the life of,

00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:50.760 align:middle line:90%
you wouldn't trade places today.

00:05:50.760 --> 00:05:53.052 align:middle line:84%
So what's the drawback of if
it would've been that way?

00:05:53.052 --> 00:05:55.400 align:middle line:84%
And he broke down in
tears and had affection

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:57.560 align:middle line:84%
for his father for the
first time since he was 16.

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:59.210 align:middle line:90%
He was 42.

00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:01.220 align:middle line:84%
So he was comparing his
life, all those years,

00:06:01.220 --> 00:06:03.137 align:middle line:84%
to what he thought it
should have been instead

00:06:03.137 --> 00:06:04.440 align:middle line:90%
of embracing the way it is.

00:06:04.440 --> 00:06:06.830 align:middle line:84%
And so many people are not
embracing life and being

00:06:06.830 --> 00:06:08.780 align:middle line:84%
grateful for life the
way it is, and keep

00:06:08.780 --> 00:06:11.800 align:middle line:84%
comparing it to something
that doesn't exist.

00:06:11.800 --> 00:06:15.640 align:middle line:84%
>> So you're starting to answer
my next question, which is,

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:21.260 align:middle line:84%
the Demartini Method has got
some very specific underlining

00:06:21.260 --> 00:06:25.760 align:middle line:84%
values and teachings that a lot
of the more traditional methods

00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:29.540 align:middle line:84%
of psychology and
psychiatry don't have.

00:06:29.540 --> 00:06:34.010 align:middle line:84%
And from my observation, it's
what stands the Demartini

00:06:34.010 --> 00:06:37.250 align:middle line:84%
Method as being
far more effective

00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:40.082 align:middle line:84%
than perhaps some of the older,
more traditional methods.

00:06:40.082 --> 00:06:41.540 align:middle line:84%
Can you elaborate
a little bit more

00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:43.100 align:middle line:84%
as to how you
would differentiate

00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:44.240 align:middle line:90%
between those methods?

00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:45.364 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:45.364 --> 00:06:49.730 align:middle line:90%


00:06:49.730 --> 00:06:52.730 align:middle line:84%
A century or so ago, there was
a guy named Jeremy Bentham, who

00:06:52.730 --> 00:06:56.633 align:middle line:84%
created kind of a utilitarian
model of hedonism,

00:06:56.633 --> 00:06:59.300 align:middle line:84%
that we're supposed to be happy,
and supposed to be pleasureful,

00:06:59.300 --> 00:07:01.610 align:middle line:84%
and it's our birthright
to always be up, always

00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:03.770 align:middle line:90%
be positive, always be happy.

00:07:03.770 --> 00:07:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And even your grandmother
said, be nice.

00:07:05.910 --> 00:07:06.710 align:middle line:90%
Don't be mean.

00:07:06.710 --> 00:07:07.220 align:middle line:90%
Be kind.

00:07:07.220 --> 00:07:07.760 align:middle line:90%
Don't be cruel.

00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:08.360 align:middle line:90%
Be positive.

00:07:08.360 --> 00:07:08.960 align:middle line:90%
Don't be negative.

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:09.680 align:middle line:90%
Be giving.

00:07:09.680 --> 00:07:10.480 align:middle line:90%
Don't be taking.

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:11.960 align:middle line:90%
And it's all one-sided.

00:07:11.960 --> 00:07:15.020 align:middle line:84%
And yet, she ends up going
and bitching at Grandpa

00:07:15.020 --> 00:07:16.340 align:middle line:90%
and stealing from Grandpa.

00:07:16.340 --> 00:07:19.348 align:middle line:84%
So she has a
hypocrisy, in a sense.

00:07:19.348 --> 00:07:21.890 align:middle line:84%
And we have this fantasy where
it's supposed to be one-sided.

00:07:21.890 --> 00:07:25.350 align:middle line:84%
And the foundation
of psychology--

00:07:25.350 --> 00:07:26.750 align:middle line:90%
not all of it, but a lot of it--

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.130 align:middle line:90%
is animal psychology.

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:30.577 align:middle line:84%
It's avoiding the predator
and seeking the prey--

00:07:30.577 --> 00:07:31.910 align:middle line:90%
avoiding pain, seeking pleasure.

00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:33.890 align:middle line:90%
It's very hedonistic.

00:07:33.890 --> 00:07:36.320 align:middle line:84%
And the problem with that model
is, if we were to do that,

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:39.090 align:middle line:84%
and we would just eat sugar
and have sex all day long,

00:07:39.090 --> 00:07:42.260 align:middle line:84%
and we'd have diabetics
and sexual problems.

00:07:42.260 --> 00:07:46.170 align:middle line:84%
Wisdom is embracing both sides
and more objective reasoning.

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:47.870 align:middle line:84%
And when we live by
our highest values,

00:07:47.870 --> 00:07:49.347 align:middle line:84%
we have more
objective reasoning.

00:07:49.347 --> 00:07:51.680 align:middle line:84%
When we're unfulfilled in
life, we look, like an animal,

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:53.360 align:middle line:90%
for a one-sided world.

00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:56.120 align:middle line:84%
And I always say that addictive
behavior to a one-sided world

00:07:56.120 --> 00:07:59.065 align:middle line:84%
is a compensation for
unfulfilled highest values.

00:07:59.065 --> 00:08:00.440 align:middle line:84%
So when people
don't find meaning

00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:02.540 align:middle line:84%
and don't find fulfillment doing
something that's meaningful,

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:04.998 align:middle line:84%
and prioritizing their life,
and doing what really inspires

00:08:04.998 --> 00:08:07.580 align:middle line:84%
them, they'll be vulnerable
for avoiding pain and seeking

00:08:07.580 --> 00:08:08.380 align:middle line:90%
pleasure.

00:08:08.380 --> 00:08:09.830 align:middle line:84%
An entire psychological
movement--

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:12.020 align:middle line:84%
which are called shrinks,
which shrink people,

00:08:12.020 --> 00:08:14.810 align:middle line:84%
instead of stretchers,
who would stretch people--

00:08:14.810 --> 00:08:17.660 align:middle line:84%
are basically promoting that
whole animalistic model.

00:08:17.660 --> 00:08:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm offering
in the Demartini Method

00:08:19.610 --> 00:08:21.318 align:middle line:84%
is something more
transcendent than that,

00:08:21.318 --> 00:08:23.776 align:middle line:84%
something that allows people
to embrace both sides in life.

00:08:23.776 --> 00:08:25.151 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
get rid of half

00:08:25.151 --> 00:08:26.480 align:middle line:90%
of your life to love yourself.

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:28.688 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to get rid
of half of the other people

00:08:28.688 --> 00:08:29.850 align:middle line:90%
in your life to love them.

00:08:29.850 --> 00:08:31.750 align:middle line:84%
You just need to be
realistic about life.

00:08:31.750 --> 00:08:33.312 align:middle line:84%
Because it has
pain and pleasure.

00:08:33.312 --> 00:08:34.520 align:middle line:90%
It has support and challenge.

00:08:34.520 --> 00:08:36.049 align:middle line:90%
It has both sides of life.

00:08:36.049 --> 00:08:38.164 align:middle line:84%
Even the marriage ceremonies,
when you look at it,

00:08:38.164 --> 00:08:40.280 align:middle line:84%
it's sort of, for richer, for
poor, for this or for that.

00:08:40.280 --> 00:08:41.129 align:middle line:90%
It's both.

00:08:41.129 --> 00:08:41.929 align:middle line:90%
But we forget that.

00:08:41.929 --> 00:08:44.470 align:middle line:84%
And we then want it to only
support us without challenge--

00:08:44.470 --> 00:08:46.160 align:middle line:90%
ease without difficulty.

00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:48.380 align:middle line:84%
So I'm trying to ground
people and realize

00:08:48.380 --> 00:08:50.750 align:middle line:84%
that life has both sides
and embrace both sides.

00:08:50.750 --> 00:08:51.830 align:middle line:90%
Because both are needed.

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:53.520 align:middle line:84%
We don't grow if we
are only supported.

00:08:53.520 --> 00:08:55.270 align:middle line:84%
We stay juvenilely
dependent all our life.

00:08:55.270 --> 00:08:57.880 align:middle line:84%
If we get challenged, and
we get responsibilities,

00:08:57.880 --> 00:09:00.110 align:middle line:84%
we become precocious,
independent, and grow.

00:09:00.110 --> 00:09:01.040 align:middle line:90%
We need both.

00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.640 align:middle line:84%
Maximum growth and
development occurs

00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:05.570 align:middle line:84%
at the border of support and
challenge, ease and difficulty.

00:09:05.570 --> 00:09:08.375 align:middle line:84%
And real leaders are not trying
to shrink from challenge.

00:09:08.375 --> 00:09:10.750 align:middle line:84%
They go after challenges--
fill their day with challenges

00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:12.200 align:middle line:90%
that inspire them.

00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:14.010 align:middle line:84%
Because that way, their life
doesn't fill up with challenges

00:09:14.010 --> 00:09:14.810 align:middle line:90%
that don't.

00:09:14.810 --> 00:09:16.760 align:middle line:84%
So embracing both
sides of life is

00:09:16.760 --> 00:09:18.380 align:middle line:84%
the difference in
my model and the way

00:09:18.380 --> 00:09:19.380 align:middle line:90%
that I work with people.

00:09:19.380 --> 00:09:21.005 align:middle line:84%
And as a result of
it, we can transform

00:09:21.005 --> 00:09:23.120 align:middle line:84%
people that have depression
very quickly compared

00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:24.962 align:middle line:90%
to what's being used out there.

00:09:24.962 --> 00:09:27.170 align:middle line:84%
Because they're trying to
feed this fantasy in people

00:09:27.170 --> 00:09:29.990 align:middle line:90%
and polarizing people from.

00:09:29.990 --> 00:09:32.660 align:middle line:84%
>> So something you mentioned
in that was the importance

00:09:32.660 --> 00:09:35.150 align:middle line:84%
of getting really clear on
what your core values are.

00:09:35.150 --> 00:09:38.220 align:middle line:90%


00:09:38.220 --> 00:09:40.730 align:middle line:84%
First of all, how
can our audience,

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.550 align:middle line:84%
who may right now be stuck
in a place of overwhelment,

00:09:43.550 --> 00:09:47.100 align:middle line:84%
or anxiety, or in
a deep depression--

00:09:47.100 --> 00:09:49.220 align:middle line:84%
what kind of simple
exercise can they

00:09:49.220 --> 00:09:52.220 align:middle line:84%
start to do to start to
create some clearer core

00:09:52.220 --> 00:09:55.460 align:middle line:84%
values that they can then
start to work on in order

00:09:55.460 --> 00:09:58.843 align:middle line:84%
to take them closer to
understanding what creates

00:09:58.843 --> 00:10:00.260 align:middle line:84%
meaning and purpose
in their life,

00:10:00.260 --> 00:10:03.420 align:middle line:84%
so they can start to make
choices that feed that?

00:10:03.420 --> 00:10:06.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they don't need to
find values that do that.

00:10:06.470 --> 00:10:07.760 align:middle line:90%
They already have them.

00:10:07.760 --> 00:10:10.530 align:middle line:84%
Every human being lives by a set
of priorities, a set of values

00:10:10.530 --> 00:10:11.540 align:middle line:90%
already.

00:10:11.540 --> 00:10:13.315 align:middle line:84%
And we have this idea
that we're supposed

00:10:13.315 --> 00:10:14.690 align:middle line:84%
to pick them up
from our parents,

00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:16.695 align:middle line:84%
or get it from
society, or whatever.

00:10:16.695 --> 00:10:19.070 align:middle line:84%
But the people that really
made a difference in the world

00:10:19.070 --> 00:10:21.020 align:middle line:84%
are not the people
that fit into society.

00:10:21.020 --> 00:10:22.395 align:middle line:84%
The people that
make a difference

00:10:22.395 --> 00:10:24.618 align:middle line:84%
are the people that are
transcending the implications

00:10:24.618 --> 00:10:26.660 align:middle line:84%
that society is always
imposing-- traditionalism,

00:10:26.660 --> 00:10:27.350 align:middle line:90%
conventionalism.

00:10:27.350 --> 00:10:28.400 align:middle line:84%
It's the people
that do something

00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:30.140 align:middle line:84%
beyond that that
actually contribute

00:10:30.140 --> 00:10:31.980 align:middle line:90%
to the growth of society.

00:10:31.980 --> 00:10:34.490 align:middle line:84%
So it's not about trying
to get them into this

00:10:34.490 --> 00:10:35.930 align:middle line:90%
or try to find them that way.

00:10:35.930 --> 00:10:37.565 align:middle line:84%
It's looking at our
life and looking

00:10:37.565 --> 00:10:38.815 align:middle line:90%
at what our life demonstrates.

00:10:38.815 --> 00:10:41.780 align:middle line:84%
Because our life demonstrates
our values already, right now.

00:10:41.780 --> 00:10:43.670 align:middle line:84%
So you look at how
you fill your space.

00:10:43.670 --> 00:10:45.410 align:middle line:84%
You look at how you
spend your time.

00:10:45.410 --> 00:10:47.900 align:middle line:84%
You look at what
you're energized by.

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:49.610 align:middle line:84%
You look at what you
spend your money on.

00:10:49.610 --> 00:10:51.170 align:middle line:84%
You look at where
you're organized.

00:10:51.170 --> 00:10:52.790 align:middle line:84%
You look at where you're
disciplined, and reliable,

00:10:52.790 --> 00:10:53.780 align:middle line:90%
and focused.

00:10:53.780 --> 00:10:56.270 align:middle line:84%
You look at what you think
about, and visualize, and talk

00:10:56.270 --> 00:10:58.850 align:middle line:84%
to yourself about most that's
coming true in your life.

00:10:58.850 --> 00:11:00.590 align:middle line:84%
You look at what you want to
converse with other people

00:11:00.590 --> 00:11:01.490 align:middle line:90%
about.

00:11:01.490 --> 00:11:03.590 align:middle line:84%
And you look also at
the goals that you

00:11:03.590 --> 00:11:05.965 align:middle line:84%
have that are consistent and
persistent that you achieve.

00:11:05.965 --> 00:11:08.465 align:middle line:84%
And then look at what it is you
love learning, and studying,

00:11:08.465 --> 00:11:09.680 align:middle line:90%
and reading about most.

00:11:09.680 --> 00:11:10.722 align:middle line:90%
Those are the indicators.

00:11:10.722 --> 00:11:12.263 align:middle line:84%
Those are the value
determinants that

00:11:12.263 --> 00:11:14.180 align:middle line:84%
reveal to you what's
really important to you.

00:11:14.180 --> 00:11:15.555 align:middle line:84%
And the second
you set goals that

00:11:15.555 --> 00:11:18.140 align:middle line:84%
are aligned with that highest
value, the things that

00:11:18.140 --> 00:11:20.150 align:middle line:84%
are really important,
you're more objective,

00:11:20.150 --> 00:11:22.895 align:middle line:84%
you're more realistic, you're
more resilient and adaptable.

00:11:22.895 --> 00:11:24.020 align:middle line:90%
You tend to achieve things.

00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:26.810 align:middle line:84%
You tend to set goals
that are more manageable.

00:11:26.810 --> 00:11:28.183 align:middle line:90%
You have your self governance.

00:11:28.183 --> 00:11:30.350 align:middle line:84%
The executive center in the
brain, the telencephalon

00:11:30.350 --> 00:11:33.590 align:middle line:84%
comes online, and self-governs
you, and makes you strategic,

00:11:33.590 --> 00:11:37.247 align:middle line:84%
and visionary, and really
go out there and execute.

00:11:37.247 --> 00:11:39.080 align:middle line:84%
But if you don't live
by the highest values,

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:41.275 align:middle line:84%
the unfulfilled activates
the amygdala area

00:11:41.275 --> 00:11:43.650 align:middle line:84%
of the brain which wants to
avoid pain and seek pleasure.

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:44.912 align:middle line:90%
It's the animal brain.

00:11:44.912 --> 00:11:46.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
most psychology is.

00:11:46.370 --> 00:11:47.960 align:middle line:84%
And that's where most
people are trapped.

00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:49.330 align:middle line:84%
They're looking for
a one-sided world,

00:11:49.330 --> 00:11:50.260 align:middle line:90%
trying to avoid the other side.

00:11:50.260 --> 00:11:52.330 align:middle line:84%
And they're running around
this anxiety and fear

00:11:52.330 --> 00:11:53.890 align:middle line:84%
all the time because
they're holding

00:11:53.890 --> 00:11:55.640 align:middle line:84%
onto a fantasy
about how life is.

00:11:55.640 --> 00:11:56.827 align:middle line:90%
And the other side's there.

00:11:56.827 --> 00:11:58.660 align:middle line:84%
It's like trying to
have a two-sided magnet.

00:11:58.660 --> 00:11:59.830 align:middle line:84%
And they're wanting
to get one side

00:11:59.830 --> 00:12:01.870 align:middle line:84%
and then the other side
keeps following you around.

00:12:01.870 --> 00:12:03.010 align:middle line:84%
Because they were
expecting to get

00:12:03.010 --> 00:12:04.210 align:middle line:84%
rid of the other
side of the magnet.

00:12:04.210 --> 00:12:05.790 align:middle line:84%
And the other side's there,
and I don't want that.

00:12:05.790 --> 00:12:07.415 align:middle line:84%
So they're fearful
of that other magnet

00:12:07.415 --> 00:12:09.220 align:middle line:90%
side coming, when they need it.

00:12:09.220 --> 00:12:10.640 align:middle line:90%
They need it to grow.

00:12:10.640 --> 00:12:14.200 align:middle line:84%
So I'm interested in helping
people find their own values,

00:12:14.200 --> 00:12:15.420 align:middle line:90%
their highest values.

00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:17.383 align:middle line:84%
On my website, I
have a tool on there

00:12:17.383 --> 00:12:18.550 align:middle line:90%
that they can follow simply.

00:12:18.550 --> 00:12:19.630 align:middle line:90%
It's free.

00:12:19.630 --> 00:12:20.650 align:middle line:90%
Drdemartini.com.

00:12:20.650 --> 00:12:23.273 align:middle line:84%
They can go on there, and
learn how to find their values,

00:12:23.273 --> 00:12:25.690 align:middle line:84%
and start orchestrating, and
prioritizing, and structuring

00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:26.920 align:middle line:90%
their life accordingly.

00:12:26.920 --> 00:12:28.600 align:middle line:84%
When they do, they're
more resilient.

00:12:28.600 --> 00:12:30.580 align:middle line:84%
They're more realistic
in their expectations.

00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:31.398 align:middle line:90%
They achieve more.

00:12:31.398 --> 00:12:32.440 align:middle line:90%
Their self worth goes up.

00:12:32.440 --> 00:12:34.450 align:middle line:90%
Their internal dialogue changes.

00:12:34.450 --> 00:12:36.220 align:middle line:84%
They are saying thank
you for life instead

00:12:36.220 --> 00:12:39.250 align:middle line:90%
of the other things in life.

00:12:39.250 --> 00:12:43.510 align:middle line:84%
>> So in your experience--
and I know how many hundreds

00:12:43.510 --> 00:12:45.640 align:middle line:84%
of thousands of people that
you've helped transform

00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:47.350 align:middle line:90%
their lives--

00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:50.800 align:middle line:84%
have you observed a
certain belief system

00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:53.170 align:middle line:84%
that is common amongst
those that suffer

00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:54.850 align:middle line:90%
from depression or anxiety?

00:12:54.850 --> 00:12:55.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:12:55.940 --> 00:12:59.410 align:middle line:84%
They're expecting to live
in other people's values

00:12:59.410 --> 00:13:01.745 align:middle line:84%
and they're trying to live
outside their own values.

00:13:01.745 --> 00:13:04.120 align:middle line:84%
Or they're expecting other
people to live in their values

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:05.980 align:middle line:90%
or outside their values.

00:13:05.980 --> 00:13:08.650 align:middle line:84%
Or they're expecting the world
to be a one-sided world, which

00:13:08.650 --> 00:13:09.630 align:middle line:90%
is not possible.

00:13:09.630 --> 00:13:11.770 align:middle line:84%
Or they're expecting
mechanical objects

00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:14.800 align:middle line:84%
to work in a way that
matches their fantasy.

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:16.550 align:middle line:84%
So they have unrealistic
expectations.

00:13:16.550 --> 00:13:18.410 align:middle line:84%
There's 15 most
common ones that I

00:13:18.410 --> 00:13:20.620 align:middle line:90%
found that lead to depression.

00:13:20.620 --> 00:13:24.130 align:middle line:84%
The unrealistic expectation
that the people around them

00:13:24.130 --> 00:13:25.653 align:middle line:90%
are supposed to be one-sided.

00:13:25.653 --> 00:13:28.070 align:middle line:84%
They're always supposed to be
nice, not mean, always kind,

00:13:28.070 --> 00:13:30.040 align:middle line:90%
not cruel, giving, not taking.

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:31.130 align:middle line:90%
Nobody's that way.

00:13:31.130 --> 00:13:32.260 align:middle line:90%
I'm not nice.

00:13:32.260 --> 00:13:33.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm nice and mean.

00:13:33.520 --> 00:13:34.480 align:middle line:90%
I'm kind and cruel.

00:13:34.480 --> 00:13:35.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm generous and stingy.

00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:36.610 align:middle line:90%
I'm everything.

00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:39.010 align:middle line:84%
I've learned that I
have all 4,628 traits

00:13:39.010 --> 00:13:41.370 align:middle line:84%
that I've ever found in
the "Oxford Dictionary."

00:13:41.370 --> 00:13:43.120 align:middle line:84%
So if you expect
somebody to be one-sided,

00:13:43.120 --> 00:13:47.050 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have what I
call the ABCDs of negativity--

00:13:47.050 --> 00:13:50.200 align:middle line:84%
Anger and Aggression, Blame
and Betrayal, Criticism

00:13:50.200 --> 00:13:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and Challenge, Despair
and Depression.

00:13:52.060 --> 00:13:53.930 align:middle line:90%
Add E-- Exit and Escape.

00:13:53.930 --> 00:13:55.720 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
want escape life.

00:13:55.720 --> 00:13:58.030 align:middle line:84%
Those ABCDEs of
negativity are a byproduct

00:13:58.030 --> 00:13:59.860 align:middle line:84%
of having unrealistic
expectations.

00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.410 align:middle line:84%
Then, you're expecting other
people to live in your values

00:14:02.410 --> 00:14:03.850 align:middle line:90%
or outside their own values.

00:14:03.850 --> 00:14:05.530 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be angry now
for that because that's not

00:14:05.530 --> 00:14:06.430 align:middle line:90%
going to happen.

00:14:06.430 --> 00:14:08.200 align:middle line:84%
Because they make decisions
based on their values.

00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:09.700 align:middle line:84%
Then you're going
to expect yourself

00:14:09.700 --> 00:14:12.682 align:middle line:84%
to live outside your values
or in a one-sided world.

00:14:12.682 --> 00:14:14.140 align:middle line:84%
Or you're expecting
the world to be

00:14:14.140 --> 00:14:16.110 align:middle line:84%
that way, or live in your
values-- the whole world's

00:14:16.110 --> 00:14:17.360 align:middle line:90%
supposed to match your values.

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:18.630 align:middle line:90%
These are delusions.

00:14:18.630 --> 00:14:20.680 align:middle line:84%
Or you're expecting
objects, mechanical things,

00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:22.240 align:middle line:84%
to work the way you
fantasize instead

00:14:22.240 --> 00:14:23.650 align:middle line:90%
of the way they're designed.

00:14:23.650 --> 00:14:26.260 align:middle line:84%
So anytime you have all these
unrealistic expectations,

00:14:26.260 --> 00:14:28.090 align:middle line:84%
depression is a
feedback mechanism

00:14:28.090 --> 00:14:29.800 align:middle line:84%
to let you know that
you're projecting

00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:31.630 align:middle line:84%
unrealistic expectations
onto the world,

00:14:31.630 --> 00:14:33.760 align:middle line:84%
and onto people,
and onto yourself.

00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:36.480 align:middle line:84%
And the second you stop that,
and set realistic expectations,

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.350 align:middle line:84%
you're depression
doesn't have to be there.

00:14:38.350 --> 00:14:39.880 align:middle line:90%
It's not a disease.

00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:41.770 align:middle line:84%
It's a normal,
biological response

00:14:41.770 --> 00:14:43.960 align:middle line:90%
to unrealistic expectations.

00:14:43.960 --> 00:14:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I'm
hearing there, then--

00:14:45.460 --> 00:14:50.860 align:middle line:84%
that part of the pivotal point
of change is to choose to no

00:14:50.860 --> 00:14:52.990 align:middle line:84%
longer be of victim
consciousness

00:14:52.990 --> 00:14:54.610 align:middle line:90%
of your circumstances.

00:14:54.610 --> 00:14:57.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I've never seen a
victim consciousness who blames

00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:58.030 align:middle line:90%
people.

00:14:58.030 --> 00:14:59.550 align:middle line:84%
People who blame
things on the outside

00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:00.883 align:middle line:90%
look for saviors on the outside.

00:15:00.883 --> 00:15:03.383 align:middle line:84%
They look for things
out there to save them.

00:15:03.383 --> 00:15:05.050 align:middle line:84%
And they become
addicted to those things

00:15:05.050 --> 00:15:07.050 align:middle line:84%
they think is going to
save them from this thing

00:15:07.050 --> 00:15:08.170 align:middle line:90%
that they're blaming.

00:15:08.170 --> 00:15:09.953 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen that
make empowerment.

00:15:09.953 --> 00:15:11.620 align:middle line:84%
I've seen people take
on accountability,

00:15:11.620 --> 00:15:13.690 align:middle line:84%
and take on their own
cause and their own effect,

00:15:13.690 --> 00:15:16.300 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden,
transform their perception.

00:15:16.300 --> 00:15:19.770 align:middle line:84%
William James basically said
that the greatest discovery

00:15:19.770 --> 00:15:21.520 align:middle line:84%
of his generation is
that human beings can

00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.520 align:middle line:84%
alter their lives by
alternating the perceptions

00:15:23.520 --> 00:15:24.520 align:middle line:90%
and attitudes of mind.

00:15:24.520 --> 00:15:25.640 align:middle line:90%
I find that to be true.

00:15:25.640 --> 00:15:26.590 align:middle line:90%
You can change your perception.

00:15:26.590 --> 00:15:28.390 align:middle line:84%
Every weekend in "The
Breakthrough Experience,"

00:15:28.390 --> 00:15:30.340 align:middle line:84%
I have people with the
most horrendous stuff

00:15:30.340 --> 00:15:31.560 align:middle line:90%
that they've had in life.

00:15:31.560 --> 00:15:33.020 align:middle line:84%
And yet, they're willing
to run stories over,

00:15:33.020 --> 00:15:34.190 align:middle line:84%
and they want to
be victims of it,

00:15:34.190 --> 00:15:35.650 align:middle line:84%
and they want to just go
on, and on, and on about it.

00:15:35.650 --> 00:15:37.900 align:middle line:84%
And I stopped the story
because it validates the brain

00:15:37.900 --> 00:15:38.987 align:middle line:90%
and keeps them stuck.

00:15:38.987 --> 00:15:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And I say, let's look at it
from a different perspective

00:15:41.320 --> 00:15:43.150 align:middle line:90%
and ask, how does it serve you?

00:15:43.150 --> 00:15:44.920 align:middle line:84%
And if it had not happened,
what would've been the drawback?

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:46.212 align:middle line:90%
And ask a new set of questions.

00:15:46.212 --> 00:15:48.023 align:middle line:84%
I have 48 questions
that I ask people.

00:15:48.023 --> 00:15:49.690 align:middle line:84%
And when, all of a
sudden, they're done,

00:15:49.690 --> 00:15:51.820 align:middle line:84%
they're in tears of gratitude
from the same event.

00:15:51.820 --> 00:15:53.320 align:middle line:84%
It had nothing to
do with the event.

00:15:53.320 --> 00:15:55.180 align:middle line:84%
It's all about the
perception of the event.

00:15:55.180 --> 00:15:56.170 align:middle line:84%
And then, all of
a sudden, instead

00:15:56.170 --> 00:15:57.790 align:middle line:84%
of blaming the
environment or whatever

00:15:57.790 --> 00:15:59.860 align:middle line:84%
that had caused their
problem, or they're

00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:02.080 align:middle line:84%
blaming their parents, or
their family dynamics--

00:16:02.080 --> 00:16:03.250 align:middle line:90%
I hear this all the time.

00:16:03.250 --> 00:16:04.050 align:middle line:90%
They change it.

00:16:04.050 --> 00:16:05.380 align:middle line:84%
And then they're
thankful for that.

00:16:05.380 --> 00:16:07.380 align:middle line:84%
Anything you can't say
thank you for is baggage.

00:16:07.380 --> 00:16:09.180 align:middle line:84%
Anything you can say
thank you for is fuel.

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:09.980 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:16:09.980 --> 00:16:10.880 align:middle line:90%
That's powerful.

00:16:10.880 --> 00:16:11.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:12.190 align:middle line:90%
>> That's really powerful.

00:16:12.190 --> 00:16:14.732 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm very grateful to be able
to work with people and watch

00:16:14.732 --> 00:16:15.800 align:middle line:90%
this happen--

00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:17.823 align:middle line:84%
very inspiring to watch
the light bulbs go on,

00:16:17.823 --> 00:16:19.240 align:middle line:84%
and people all of
a sudden realize

00:16:19.240 --> 00:16:20.740 align:middle line:84%
that there's nothing
wrong with them

00:16:20.740 --> 00:16:23.198 align:middle line:84%
and there's nothing wrong with
what happened in their life.

00:16:23.198 --> 00:16:24.370 align:middle line:90%
It's just an experience.

00:16:24.370 --> 00:16:25.180 align:middle line:90%
It's an event.

00:16:25.180 --> 00:16:28.060 align:middle line:84%
>> That's the other thing
that I love about your work,

00:16:28.060 --> 00:16:32.950 align:middle line:84%
is that it just completely takes
the stigma out of there being

00:16:32.950 --> 00:16:35.110 align:middle line:90%
a mental health problem.

00:16:35.110 --> 00:16:37.750 align:middle line:84%
When you look at it as
a feedback mechanism,

00:16:37.750 --> 00:16:39.837 align:middle line:84%
to give you feedback as
to basically, what you do

00:16:39.837 --> 00:16:41.170 align:middle line:90%
want versus what you don't want.

00:16:41.170 --> 00:16:43.420 align:middle line:84%
>> I really believe that all
of the signs and symptoms

00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:45.940 align:middle line:84%
of our body are feedback
mechanisms to guide us to live

00:16:45.940 --> 00:16:47.070 align:middle line:90%
authentically.

00:16:47.070 --> 00:16:49.650 align:middle line:84%
And that sounds kind
of broad, but really

00:16:49.650 --> 00:16:53.050 align:middle line:84%
going into the depth of what
that means is very significant.

00:16:53.050 --> 00:16:56.180 align:middle line:84%
Very commonly, I have people
come to me in "The Breakthrough

00:16:56.180 --> 00:16:58.980 align:middle line:84%
Experience" and they say, well,
I have a biochemical imbalance.

00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:01.712 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I have
bipolar, or schizoid behavior,

00:17:01.712 --> 00:17:03.420 align:middle line:84%
or dissociative
disorder-- all this stuff

00:17:03.420 --> 00:17:05.900 align:middle line:84%
is because I have a biochemical
imbalance in the brain.

00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:06.700 align:middle line:90%
And I go, OK.

00:17:06.700 --> 00:17:07.500 align:middle line:90%
That's fine.

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:08.579 align:middle line:90%
But I explained to them.

00:17:08.579 --> 00:17:10.950 align:middle line:84%
I said, imagine
being in this room.

00:17:10.950 --> 00:17:13.310 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I open up the door.

00:17:13.310 --> 00:17:16.069 align:middle line:84%
And a giant tiger jumps in,
and leaps across the room,

00:17:16.069 --> 00:17:17.069 align:middle line:90%
and is going toward you.

00:17:17.069 --> 00:17:20.280 align:middle line:84%
And it's got its fangs out, and
it's about to eat your head.

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:21.422 align:middle line:90%
And you turn, and you look.

00:17:21.422 --> 00:17:22.380 align:middle line:90%
And you go, oh my god--

00:17:22.380 --> 00:17:23.180 align:middle line:90%
tiger!

00:17:23.180 --> 00:17:24.450 align:middle line:90%
And you protect yourself.

00:17:24.450 --> 00:17:26.970 align:middle line:84%
If we stop and got a
"Men in Black" pen--

00:17:26.970 --> 00:17:29.940 align:middle line:84%
stopped everything, and all
of a sudden say, all right,

00:17:29.940 --> 00:17:32.550 align:middle line:84%
let's go and do a
biochemistry on their brain,

00:17:32.550 --> 00:17:34.960 align:middle line:84%
we would find that
the dopamine is low,

00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:39.600 align:middle line:84%
the enkephalins are down,
serotonin has dropped.

00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:42.780 align:middle line:84%
Vasopressin, oxytocin,
estrogen are all dropped.

00:17:42.780 --> 00:17:46.075 align:middle line:84%
And epinephrine, norepinephrine,
testosterone, histamine,

00:17:46.075 --> 00:17:48.450 align:middle line:84%
substance P, and all these
other chemistries in the brain

00:17:48.450 --> 00:17:49.950 align:middle line:90%
are all skyrocketing.

00:17:49.950 --> 00:17:52.080 align:middle line:84%
Right there, on the spot,
from that perception,

00:17:52.080 --> 00:17:53.190 align:middle line:90%
change chemistry.

00:17:53.190 --> 00:17:55.030 align:middle line:84%
So if we freeze
frame it, we'd find

00:17:55.030 --> 00:17:56.968 align:middle line:90%
that biochemical imbalance, see?

00:17:56.968 --> 00:17:59.010 align:middle line:84%
Because they're imagining
being eaten by a tiger.

00:17:59.010 --> 00:18:01.042 align:middle line:84%
So their perception has
lied, thinking they're

00:18:01.042 --> 00:18:02.250 align:middle line:90%
going to be eaten by a tiger.

00:18:02.250 --> 00:18:05.400 align:middle line:84%
Then, if I take the pen and
stop, and let the tiger come,

00:18:05.400 --> 00:18:09.150 align:middle line:84%
and it jumps, and it licks them,
and it tells them it's Tony

00:18:09.150 --> 00:18:13.150 align:middle line:84%
Tiger, and it hugs
them, all of a sudden,

00:18:13.150 --> 00:18:15.450 align:middle line:84%
the person then-- we stop,
freeze frame it again,

00:18:15.450 --> 00:18:17.310 align:middle line:84%
and actually, they
go, oh my god--

00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:18.450 align:middle line:90%
a little, beautiful tiger.

00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:19.763 align:middle line:90%
It's my little, pet tiger.

00:18:19.763 --> 00:18:21.930 align:middle line:84%
And we go and we see the
complete opposite chemistry

00:18:21.930 --> 00:18:23.010 align:middle line:90%
occur.

00:18:23.010 --> 00:18:25.230 align:middle line:84%
So if it is
biochemistry by itself,

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:27.632 align:middle line:90%
how can it change that quick?

00:18:27.632 --> 00:18:29.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, everybody has
had this experience

00:18:29.340 --> 00:18:30.820 align:middle line:90%
where they're sitting at home.

00:18:30.820 --> 00:18:31.620 align:middle line:90%
It's a weekend.

00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:33.310 align:middle line:84%
The husband and
wife are fighting.

00:18:33.310 --> 00:18:34.950 align:middle line:90%
They're having this quarrel.

00:18:34.950 --> 00:18:37.297 align:middle line:84%
And they're really
at each other.

00:18:37.297 --> 00:18:38.880 align:middle line:84%
They're really going
after each other.

00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:40.320 align:middle line:84%
And then, all of the
sudden, the doorbell rings.

00:18:40.320 --> 00:18:41.700 align:middle line:84%
And a friend they
haven't seen in 20 years

00:18:41.700 --> 00:18:42.600 align:middle line:90%
goes in the doorbell.

00:18:42.600 --> 00:18:44.240 align:middle line:84%
Just happened to be
the neighborhood!

00:18:44.240 --> 00:18:46.650 align:middle line:84%
And they stop the
fighting and go, hi!

00:18:46.650 --> 00:18:49.050 align:middle line:84%
They put on a facade,
and they suppress that.

00:18:49.050 --> 00:18:51.930 align:middle line:84%
And it goes now unconscious
and subconscious.

00:18:51.930 --> 00:18:54.750 align:middle line:84%
And then for two hours and
hang out with their friends.

00:18:54.750 --> 00:18:56.700 align:middle line:84%
And they never get back
to complete the fight,

00:18:56.700 --> 00:18:58.830 align:middle line:84%
but they've still got
memories and stored

00:18:58.830 --> 00:19:00.660 align:middle line:84%
secondary and
tertiary associations

00:19:00.660 --> 00:19:02.610 align:middle line:90%
to that original event.

00:19:02.610 --> 00:19:05.032 align:middle line:84%
And so now, what happens
is all that's subconscious.

00:19:05.032 --> 00:19:07.240 align:middle line:84%
And they go about their
business and everything else.

00:19:07.240 --> 00:19:09.990 align:middle line:84%
And now, almost anything can
trigger that original memory

00:19:09.990 --> 00:19:11.800 align:middle line:90%
that's never been balanced.

00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:14.250 align:middle line:84%
And so, those things drive
biochemistries and leave

00:19:14.250 --> 00:19:16.620 align:middle line:84%
people in biochemical
imbalance, not

00:19:16.620 --> 00:19:18.860 align:middle line:84%
because it's just randomly
there-- the biochemistry

00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:20.157 align:middle line:90%
in the brain is not working.

00:19:20.157 --> 00:19:21.990 align:middle line:84%
It's because we've
accumulated a whole bunch

00:19:21.990 --> 00:19:24.168 align:middle line:84%
of unconscious and
subconscious stuff

00:19:24.168 --> 00:19:26.460 align:middle line:84%
that we've never neutralized,
and balanced in our life,

00:19:26.460 --> 00:19:29.268 align:middle line:84%
and seen in a
balanced perspective.

00:19:29.268 --> 00:19:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And so it's sitting there,
running our chemistry.

00:19:31.310 --> 00:19:35.760 align:middle line:84%
And we don't have a way of
testing that real mind state.

00:19:35.760 --> 00:19:37.370 align:middle line:84%
All we're looking
at is chemistry.

00:19:37.370 --> 00:19:41.130 align:middle line:84%
And that's the problem with
some of the psychiatric work.

00:19:41.130 --> 00:19:43.100 align:middle line:84%
They find that there's
a zebra in the bathtub,

00:19:43.100 --> 00:19:44.468 align:middle line:90%
but they don't ask why.

00:19:44.468 --> 00:19:45.510 align:middle line:90%
They measure the stripes.

00:19:45.510 --> 00:19:46.340 align:middle line:90%
They measure the dung.

00:19:46.340 --> 00:19:48.040 align:middle line:84%
They might measure the length of
the zebra, but they don't ask,

00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:49.860 align:middle line:84%
why is there a zebra
in the bathtub?

00:19:49.860 --> 00:19:51.665 align:middle line:84%
Why is there a
biochemistry imbalance?

00:19:51.665 --> 00:19:53.040 align:middle line:84%
It's because of
those imbalances,

00:19:53.040 --> 00:19:54.120 align:middle line:84%
and they've never
been addressed.

00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:55.662 align:middle line:84%
Because we go in
there and neutralize

00:19:55.662 --> 00:19:58.410 align:middle line:84%
those with the Demartini Method,
and we change chemistries.

00:19:58.410 --> 00:19:59.910 align:middle line:84%
They go, well,
something's happened.

00:19:59.910 --> 00:20:00.750 align:middle line:90%
Your brain changed.

00:20:00.750 --> 00:20:05.340 align:middle line:84%
>> So I was just about to ask,
what in the Demartini Method

00:20:05.340 --> 00:20:08.040 align:middle line:84%
enables you to help
somebody who's in a place

00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:14.340 align:middle line:84%
of subconscious or unaware of
the past emotional experiences

00:20:14.340 --> 00:20:16.620 align:middle line:84%
that they are still
biochemically responding

00:20:16.620 --> 00:20:18.390 align:middle line:90%
to by other triggers?

00:20:18.390 --> 00:20:20.700 align:middle line:84%
What's the process that you
take people through that--

00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:22.030 align:middle line:84%
>> You've got a number
of ways of doing it.

00:20:22.030 --> 00:20:23.970 align:middle line:84%
You can actually go back
and peel the onion back,

00:20:23.970 --> 00:20:26.550 align:middle line:84%
layer by layer, and eventually
get to these core issues that

00:20:26.550 --> 00:20:27.392 align:middle line:90%
are back there.

00:20:27.392 --> 00:20:29.850 align:middle line:84%
You can ask them their history,
and sometimes their history

00:20:29.850 --> 00:20:32.010 align:middle line:84%
can reveal what this
thing was triggered by.

00:20:32.010 --> 00:20:33.840 align:middle line:84%
You can look at
anxieties because anxiety

00:20:33.840 --> 00:20:37.140 align:middle line:84%
is secondary and tertiary
compounding of original events

00:20:37.140 --> 00:20:38.583 align:middle line:90%
that have never been balanced.

00:20:38.583 --> 00:20:40.500 align:middle line:84%
Now, things are reminding
you of those events,

00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:43.320 align:middle line:84%
and they're not even aware that
those things are associated

00:20:43.320 --> 00:20:45.000 align:middle line:90%
with the original event.

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:46.560 align:middle line:90%
We had a young boy that--

00:20:46.560 --> 00:20:48.480 align:middle line:84%
his mother and
father were fighting.

00:20:48.480 --> 00:20:50.280 align:middle line:84%
And the father was
wearing a white shirt,

00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:52.940 align:middle line:84%
had brown hair, brown
mustache, blue jeans.

00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:55.240 align:middle line:84%
And they they're fighting,
and he got really aggressive

00:20:55.240 --> 00:20:56.040 align:middle line:90%
to the mother.

00:20:56.040 --> 00:20:57.457 align:middle line:84%
The child didn't
want to see that,

00:20:57.457 --> 00:21:00.360 align:middle line:84%
and it went and crawled into
its room, and covered its ears,

00:21:00.360 --> 00:21:02.850 align:middle line:84%
and closed its eyes,
and hid under the bed.

00:21:02.850 --> 00:21:04.380 align:middle line:90%
So it was associated--

00:21:04.380 --> 00:21:08.070 align:middle line:84%
that image with pain,
seeing Mommy get hurt.

00:21:08.070 --> 00:21:09.810 align:middle line:84%
So the next day, Daddy
went off to work,

00:21:09.810 --> 00:21:12.320 align:middle line:84%
and Mommy took the boy
to the grocery store.

00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:14.820 align:middle line:84%
But now, at the grocery store,
there's a man with blue jeans

00:21:14.820 --> 00:21:17.070 align:middle line:84%
and a white shirt with
brown hair and a mustache.

00:21:17.070 --> 00:21:18.870 align:middle line:84%
The second he came
down the aisle,

00:21:18.870 --> 00:21:22.080 align:middle line:84%
the baby got in front of the
mother to protect the mother,

00:21:22.080 --> 00:21:24.090 align:middle line:84%
and turned around, and
started making a tantrum

00:21:24.090 --> 00:21:25.230 align:middle line:90%
to get the mother away.

00:21:25.230 --> 00:21:26.980 align:middle line:84%
So this was a
secondary association

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:28.470 align:middle line:90%
with the primary event.

00:21:28.470 --> 00:21:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And these things
can go tertiary,

00:21:29.970 --> 00:21:32.280 align:middle line:84%
and quaternary, and they
can just keep compounding,

00:21:32.280 --> 00:21:33.780 align:middle line:84%
and now, all of a sudden,
a guy with blue jeans

00:21:33.780 --> 00:21:35.280 align:middle line:84%
and a yellow shirt
with brown hair,

00:21:35.280 --> 00:21:38.310 align:middle line:84%
or now a guy with a white shirt,
blond hair, and blue jeans.

00:21:38.310 --> 00:21:39.685 align:middle line:84%
There's different
things that can

00:21:39.685 --> 00:21:40.950 align:middle line:90%
make secondary associations.

00:21:40.950 --> 00:21:42.408 align:middle line:84%
After a while, we
don't even know

00:21:42.408 --> 00:21:43.950 align:middle line:84%
all of the things
that are triggering

00:21:43.950 --> 00:21:45.992 align:middle line:84%
the original event that's
making us feel anxious,

00:21:45.992 --> 00:21:47.520 align:middle line:84%
and it's raising
our blood pressure,

00:21:47.520 --> 00:21:50.210 align:middle line:84%
and it's causing these
changes and chemistry changes.

00:21:50.210 --> 00:21:51.710 align:middle line:84%
And then, we go to
the psychiatrist.

00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:53.740 align:middle line:84%
And he says, well, you have a
biochemical imbalance again.

00:21:53.740 --> 00:21:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And you have these
imbalanced things.

00:21:55.140 --> 00:21:56.557 align:middle line:84%
We've got to change
your chemistry

00:21:56.557 --> 00:21:58.700 align:middle line:90%
and give this anti-anxiety pill.

00:21:58.700 --> 00:21:59.500 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's fine.

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:01.340 align:middle line:90%
That's a quick pill, for real.

00:22:01.340 --> 00:22:03.525 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is, you
have command over your life.

00:22:03.525 --> 00:22:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And if you want to give
it away, that's fine.

00:22:05.400 --> 00:22:07.940 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to take
command, there's work involved.

00:22:07.940 --> 00:22:09.400 align:middle line:84%
And most people don't
want to do the work.

00:22:09.400 --> 00:22:10.730 align:middle line:84%
But if they do the work,
they can give themselves

00:22:10.730 --> 00:22:11.917 align:middle line:90%
their power back.

00:22:11.917 --> 00:22:13.000 align:middle line:90%
And I'd rather work there.

00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:15.620 align:middle line:84%
I'd rather help people
reclaim their power

00:22:15.620 --> 00:22:19.100 align:middle line:84%
than give them blame on the
outside and a magic pill

00:22:19.100 --> 00:22:20.600 align:middle line:90%
from the outside.

00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:23.690 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I've seen, and
experienced as well from

00:22:23.690 --> 00:22:25.460 align:middle line:84%
