Some of these conditions
are resolved in hours.

00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:55.100 align:middle line:90%
It's quite amazing.

00:22:55.100 --> 00:22:59.420 align:middle line:84%
But I don't label
disease as a condition.

00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:02.060 align:middle line:84%
I don't say, well, we're
treating it, or, I'm curing it.

00:23:02.060 --> 00:23:03.160 align:middle line:90%
I don't like that stamp.

00:23:03.160 --> 00:23:06.008 align:middle line:84%
I think that's creating
a label on people.

00:23:06.008 --> 00:23:07.550 align:middle line:84%
I just say that
you're a human being.

00:23:07.550 --> 00:23:08.520 align:middle line:90%
You have physiology.

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:09.905 align:middle line:90%
It's doing its job.

00:23:09.905 --> 00:23:12.840 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're having
an unrealistic expectation

00:23:12.840 --> 00:23:14.270 align:middle line:84%
and life's not
matching it, you're

00:23:14.270 --> 00:23:15.500 align:middle line:90%
going to change your chemistry.

00:23:15.500 --> 00:23:17.417 align:middle line:84%
And your chemistry is
doing what it's designed

00:23:17.417 --> 00:23:19.350 align:middle line:90%
to do in those perceptions.

00:23:19.350 --> 00:23:21.110 align:middle line:84%
So instead of seeing
it as illness,

00:23:21.110 --> 00:23:23.450 align:middle line:84%
why not see it as what your
body is designed to do,

00:23:23.450 --> 00:23:25.070 align:middle line:90%
and it's giving you a feedback?

00:23:25.070 --> 00:23:26.510 align:middle line:90%
I use the analogy--

00:23:26.510 --> 00:23:30.230 align:middle line:84%
if you went out and ate a
pizza, and then a steak,

00:23:30.230 --> 00:23:32.990 align:middle line:84%
and then a bowl of sauerkraut,
and then a cheesecake, and then

00:23:32.990 --> 00:23:35.300 align:middle line:84%
a chocolate cake, and
then a bunch of prunes,

00:23:35.300 --> 00:23:37.700 align:middle line:84%
and then some tomatoes,
and then went out

00:23:37.700 --> 00:23:39.830 align:middle line:90%
and had some beans, and--

00:23:39.830 --> 00:23:41.517 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm already
feeling the feedback.

00:23:41.517 --> 00:23:43.100 align:middle line:84%
>> The next morning,
when you wake up,

00:23:43.100 --> 00:23:44.280 align:middle line:90%
you're going to be puffy eyes.

00:23:44.280 --> 00:23:45.613 align:middle line:90%
You're going to have a headache.

00:23:45.613 --> 00:23:48.785 align:middle line:84%
You're to have bloat, and
cramps, and gas, and diarrhea,

00:23:48.785 --> 00:23:51.920 align:middle line:84%
and stomach cramps, and
nauseas, and oily skin,

00:23:51.920 --> 00:23:52.755 align:middle line:90%
and all that stuff.

00:23:52.755 --> 00:23:54.380 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you go to
some medical doctor,

00:23:54.380 --> 00:23:57.440 align:middle line:84%
he'd probably say, well,
you need an anti-flatulent,

00:23:57.440 --> 00:23:58.460 align:middle line:90%
an anti-histamine.

00:23:58.460 --> 00:24:00.770 align:middle line:90%
You need anti-cramp.

00:24:00.770 --> 00:24:01.750 align:middle line:90%
You need anti-this.

00:24:01.750 --> 00:24:03.500 align:middle line:84%
And he's giving you a
symptom because he's

00:24:03.500 --> 00:24:04.917 align:middle line:84%
trying to get rid
of your symptoms

00:24:04.917 --> 00:24:07.520 align:middle line:90%
so you can feel positive, happy.

00:24:07.520 --> 00:24:09.720 align:middle line:84%
That model is still like
the psychology model,

00:24:09.720 --> 00:24:12.050 align:middle line:84%
still trying to avoid
pain and seek pleasure.

00:24:12.050 --> 00:24:14.570 align:middle line:84%
But if you go to another
health professional that's

00:24:14.570 --> 00:24:17.600 align:middle line:84%
thinking more of a feedback
mechanism, he says,

00:24:17.600 --> 00:24:19.483 align:middle line:84%
your history shows
that you pigged out,

00:24:19.483 --> 00:24:20.900 align:middle line:84%
and your symptoms
in your body are

00:24:20.900 --> 00:24:22.530 align:middle line:90%
trying to wake you up to that.

00:24:22.530 --> 00:24:25.580 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't regulate that,
and you keep taking medication,

00:24:25.580 --> 00:24:28.080 align:middle line:84%
and you don't get the lesson,
you'll keep taking medication,

00:24:28.080 --> 00:24:28.900 align:middle line:90%
keep pigging out.

00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:29.900 align:middle line:90%
Get rid of the symptoms.

00:24:29.900 --> 00:24:31.970 align:middle line:84%
Keep pigging out,
and never grow up

00:24:31.970 --> 00:24:34.430 align:middle line:84%
and get the feedback that your
body's trying to offer you.

00:24:34.430 --> 00:24:36.888 align:middle line:84%
So I really believe that a lot
of the symptoms that we have

00:24:36.888 --> 00:24:39.590 align:middle line:84%
that we think are illness
are actually wellness,

00:24:39.590 --> 00:24:42.800 align:middle line:84%
trying to guide us back to
balanced and authentic living,

00:24:42.800 --> 00:24:45.410 align:middle line:84%
to live by our highest
values, to live fulfilled.

00:24:45.410 --> 00:24:47.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's wise to
ask those questions

00:24:47.690 --> 00:24:49.910 align:middle line:84%
and find meaning in
the disease instead

00:24:49.910 --> 00:24:52.680 align:middle line:90%
of label of the disease.

00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:54.140 align:middle line:90%
>> I love it.

00:24:54.140 --> 00:24:58.010 align:middle line:84%
So can we talk
about environment?

00:24:58.010 --> 00:25:01.040 align:middle line:84%
In my experience, often
when I'm helping people

00:25:01.040 --> 00:25:06.380 align:middle line:84%
with depression or
anxiety, because

00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:08.870 align:middle line:84%
of their mental
state at that time,

00:25:08.870 --> 00:25:11.360 align:middle line:84%
they often are not looking
after their environment.

00:25:11.360 --> 00:25:15.570 align:middle line:84%
That has a massive influence,
again, in their perception.

00:25:15.570 --> 00:25:18.590 align:middle line:84%
So what advice
can we give people

00:25:18.590 --> 00:25:20.900 align:middle line:84%
in terms of how to look
after their environment

00:25:20.900 --> 00:25:24.150 align:middle line:84%
more effectively to support
their mental and emotional

00:25:24.150 --> 00:25:24.950 align:middle line:90%
state?

00:25:24.950 --> 00:25:29.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there's a, "grant me
the wisdom to know when I can

00:25:29.960 --> 00:25:32.390 align:middle line:84%
control things and not
control things," as they say.

00:25:32.390 --> 00:25:34.307 align:middle line:84%
There's some things you
may be able to control

00:25:34.307 --> 00:25:36.800 align:middle line:84%
in your environment,
and it's wise to do so.

00:25:36.800 --> 00:25:38.900 align:middle line:84%
It's wise to bring in
order and organization,

00:25:38.900 --> 00:25:42.013 align:middle line:84%
and help you
accomplish your goals.

00:25:42.013 --> 00:25:44.555 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, if there's
nothing you can do about it,

00:25:44.555 --> 00:25:45.410 align:middle line:84%
and it's somebody
else's environment,

00:25:45.410 --> 00:25:47.877 align:middle line:84%
and you happen to be there,
you could change, and say,

00:25:47.877 --> 00:25:48.710 align:middle line:90%
thank you very much.

00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:49.918 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to stay in a hotel.

00:25:49.918 --> 00:25:52.280 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm going to grow and
become entrepreneur-like

00:25:52.280 --> 00:25:54.050 align:middle line:84%
and so I can pay
for my own life.

00:25:54.050 --> 00:25:56.720 align:middle line:84%
You could go and empower
yourself, and go and create

00:25:56.720 --> 00:25:58.063 align:middle line:90%
another environment.

00:25:58.063 --> 00:26:00.230 align:middle line:84%
Or you could go in there
and change your perception.

00:26:00.230 --> 00:26:01.710 align:middle line:84%
I always say you have
two things you can do.

00:26:01.710 --> 00:26:04.280 align:middle line:84%
You can change your actions, and
prioritize them, and delegate

00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:05.988 align:middle line:84%
lower-priority things,
and get onto doing

00:26:05.988 --> 00:26:07.340 align:middle line:90%
what's more meaningful to you.

00:26:07.340 --> 00:26:08.960 align:middle line:84%
Or you can change
your perceptions

00:26:08.960 --> 00:26:10.320 align:middle line:90%
of what's happening.

00:26:10.320 --> 00:26:11.870 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
wise to master both.

00:26:11.870 --> 00:26:13.260 align:middle line:84%
I think it's wise to
go in and take whatever

00:26:13.260 --> 00:26:14.240 align:middle line:84%
is happening in
your environment,

00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:15.920 align:middle line:90%
and find out how you can use it.

00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:17.660 align:middle line:84%
Because no matter
what happens, there's

00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:20.090 align:middle line:84%
a way of using it
to your advantage.

00:26:20.090 --> 00:26:21.860 align:middle line:84%
I had a gentleman
that was basically

00:26:21.860 --> 00:26:24.600 align:middle line:84%
bitching about his family and
how they are this and that.

00:26:24.600 --> 00:26:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And I said, so let's look at how
we can use it to our advantage.

00:26:27.410 --> 00:26:28.460 align:middle line:84%
He goes, well, there
is no advantage to it.

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:29.480 align:middle line:90%
It's crazy.

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:30.800 align:middle line:90%
I'm a dysfunctional family.

00:26:30.800 --> 00:26:31.550 align:middle line:90%
That's where I come from.

00:26:31.550 --> 00:26:33.633 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, if you want
to label that and follow

00:26:33.633 --> 00:26:34.910 align:middle line:90%
that pathway, that's fine.

00:26:34.910 --> 00:26:37.860 align:middle line:84%
That's started by John Bradshaw,
who I knew a long time ago,

00:26:37.860 --> 00:26:38.735 align:middle line:90%
and that whole model.

00:26:38.735 --> 00:26:40.110 align:middle line:84%
I said, but you
could go in there

00:26:40.110 --> 00:26:41.570 align:middle line:90%
and say, how can you use it?

00:26:41.570 --> 00:26:43.580 align:middle line:84%
And we sat down
for about two hours

00:26:43.580 --> 00:26:45.555 align:middle line:84%
and took everything
that he despised

00:26:45.555 --> 00:26:47.180 align:middle line:84%
and hated about his
environment, and we

00:26:47.180 --> 00:26:49.010 align:middle line:84%
asked how he could
use it to help him

00:26:49.010 --> 00:26:50.330 align:middle line:90%
fulfill what's most valuable.

00:26:50.330 --> 00:26:52.160 align:middle line:84%
We found out what was
valuable to his life, what

00:26:52.160 --> 00:26:53.990 align:middle line:84%
his life demonstrated
was important to him.

00:26:53.990 --> 00:26:56.960 align:middle line:84%
And we asked, how is that
experience helping him?

00:26:56.960 --> 00:26:59.390 align:middle line:90%
At first, he said, no, nothing.

00:26:59.390 --> 00:27:00.200 align:middle line:90%
Look again.

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:01.880 align:middle line:84%
Because everything
has two sides.

00:27:01.880 --> 00:27:04.030 align:middle line:84%
So what is the
benefit side to it?

00:27:04.030 --> 00:27:05.110 align:middle line:90%
And we looked for it.

00:27:05.110 --> 00:27:06.140 align:middle line:90%
And we found it.

00:27:06.140 --> 00:27:08.330 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, his
anxiety, and his stress,

00:27:08.330 --> 00:27:10.460 align:middle line:84%
and his fear about those
doing it-- because fear

00:27:10.460 --> 00:27:12.590 align:middle line:84%
is an assumption that
you're about to experience

00:27:12.590 --> 00:27:14.870 align:middle line:84%
more pain and pleasure,
more loss and gain.

00:27:14.870 --> 00:27:16.870 align:middle line:84%
But that's your perception
that's creating that.

00:27:16.870 --> 00:27:18.995 align:middle line:84%
You can change your perception
and all of a sudden,

00:27:18.995 --> 00:27:20.150 align:middle line:90%
change that whole feeling.

00:27:20.150 --> 00:27:21.350 align:middle line:90%
>> And change the biochemistry.

00:27:21.350 --> 00:27:21.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:27:21.470 --> 00:27:22.387 align:middle line:90%
Change your chemistry.

00:27:22.387 --> 00:27:24.560 align:middle line:84%
If I was to take your
thumb, put it on the table,

00:27:24.560 --> 00:27:26.450 align:middle line:84%
and take a hammer and
slam it, you'd think,

00:27:26.450 --> 00:27:27.492 align:middle line:90%
what the hell's going on?

00:27:27.492 --> 00:27:28.420 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong with you?

00:27:28.420 --> 00:27:29.690 align:middle line:90%
And you'd go, ow!

00:27:29.690 --> 00:27:30.950 align:middle line:90%
That's crazy.

00:27:30.950 --> 00:27:33.530 align:middle line:84%
But if I told you I'm going
to give you $1 billion cash

00:27:33.530 --> 00:27:35.302 align:middle line:90%
if I slam your thumb on it--

00:27:35.302 --> 00:27:37.260 align:middle line:84%
>> How many people put
their thumb right there?

00:27:37.260 --> 00:27:39.550 align:middle line:84%
>> You just say, that's
$1 billion, cash.

00:27:39.550 --> 00:27:41.360 align:middle line:90%
You go, woo!

00:27:41.360 --> 00:27:44.415 align:middle line:84%
Slam my thumb and for
$5,000, I can repair it.

00:27:44.415 --> 00:27:46.540 align:middle line:84%
And so, they take it, and
they go put it out there.

00:27:46.540 --> 00:27:48.350 align:middle line:84%
They'd actually be looking
forward to it because there's

00:27:48.350 --> 00:27:49.700 align:middle line:90%
enough reward for it.

00:27:49.700 --> 00:27:51.530 align:middle line:84%
So instead of waiting
for the rewards

00:27:51.530 --> 00:27:53.543 align:middle line:84%
out there to come
to you mysteriously,

00:27:53.543 --> 00:27:54.710 align:middle line:90%
why don't you look for them?

00:27:54.710 --> 00:27:56.127 align:middle line:84%
Why not take the
same environment,

00:27:56.127 --> 00:27:58.669 align:middle line:84%
and find out how it serves you,
and use it to your advantage?

00:27:58.669 --> 00:28:00.919 align:middle line:84%
If you can move on and say
goodbye to the environment,

00:28:00.919 --> 00:28:01.760 align:middle line:90%
great.

00:28:01.760 --> 00:28:02.990 align:middle line:84%
But if you're in
that environment

00:28:02.990 --> 00:28:05.198 align:middle line:84%
and you're not ready to move
on because you're young,

00:28:05.198 --> 00:28:06.980 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, and you're
not as empowered,

00:28:06.980 --> 00:28:08.355 align:middle line:84%
either it will
catalyze you to go

00:28:08.355 --> 00:28:10.730 align:middle line:84%
and empower you to go create
your own environment the way

00:28:10.730 --> 00:28:12.800 align:middle line:84%
you want it or you'll
find out how it serves you

00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:14.140 align:middle line:90%
and use it to your advantage.

00:28:14.140 --> 00:28:15.890 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to be
a victim of anything.

00:28:15.890 --> 00:28:17.570 align:middle line:84%
You're just asking
yourself questions.

00:28:17.570 --> 00:28:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I'm hearing
there is that there's really

00:28:20.150 --> 00:28:22.310 align:middle line:84%
an opportunity in every
moment to see the gift

00:28:22.310 --> 00:28:24.320 align:middle line:90%
in the struggle.

00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>> I really believe that the
wisdom is the instantaneous

00:28:27.410 --> 00:28:29.870 align:middle line:84%
recognition that
crisis is blessing,

00:28:29.870 --> 00:28:33.740 align:middle line:84%
that tragedy is ecstasy,
that terrible is terrific,

00:28:33.740 --> 00:28:36.887 align:middle line:84%
and all pairs of opposites
are actually one thing.

00:28:36.887 --> 00:28:38.720 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't see
it, it's because you've

00:28:38.720 --> 00:28:39.980 align:middle line:90%
chosen not to look.

00:28:39.980 --> 00:28:41.090 align:middle line:90%
It's always there.

00:28:41.090 --> 00:28:43.550 align:middle line:84%
I've yet to find somebody in
"The Breakthrough Experience"

00:28:43.550 --> 00:28:45.425 align:middle line:84%
that have had traumatic
events, or whatever--

00:28:45.425 --> 00:28:46.483 align:middle line:90%
challenging events--

00:28:46.483 --> 00:28:48.150 align:middle line:84%
that we can't find
the other side to it.

00:28:48.150 --> 00:28:49.190 align:middle line:90%
And we just keep living.

00:28:49.190 --> 00:28:50.030 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to
ruin their story.

00:28:50.030 --> 00:28:50.690 align:middle line:90%
It's not there.

00:28:50.690 --> 00:28:51.310 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to look.

00:28:51.310 --> 00:28:52.040 align:middle line:90%
They don't want to look.

00:28:52.040 --> 00:28:54.623 align:middle line:84%
But when they actually pin them
down, and get there, and look,

00:28:54.623 --> 00:28:55.630 align:middle line:90%
they find it.

00:28:55.630 --> 00:28:57.218 align:middle line:90%
So it was there the whole time.

00:28:57.218 --> 00:28:58.760 align:middle line:84%
And I always say,
why have the wisdom

00:28:58.760 --> 00:29:00.230 align:middle line:84%
of the ages with
the aging process

00:29:00.230 --> 00:29:02.580 align:middle line:84%
when you can have the wisdom
of the ages without it?

00:29:02.580 --> 00:29:04.320 align:middle line:84%
The quality of your life's based
on the quality of the questions

00:29:04.320 --> 00:29:05.120 align:middle line:90%
you ask.

00:29:05.120 --> 00:29:07.850 align:middle line:84%
If you ask questions and reveal
to you both sides of an event,

00:29:07.850 --> 00:29:10.280 align:middle line:84%
you liberate yourself
from the emotional baggage

00:29:10.280 --> 00:29:12.850 align:middle line:90%
of one-sided thinking.

00:29:12.850 --> 00:29:14.850 align:middle line:90%
>> I love it.

00:29:14.850 --> 00:29:15.650 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:29:15.650 --> 00:29:17.630 align:middle line:84%
So what I want to do,
just for a moment,

00:29:17.630 --> 00:29:20.540 align:middle line:84%
is to step more into
the corporate world

00:29:20.540 --> 00:29:24.440 align:middle line:84%
and have a look at the challenge
of corporate mental health

00:29:24.440 --> 00:29:28.190 align:middle line:84%
and the stress within
the working environment.

00:29:28.190 --> 00:29:31.280 align:middle line:84%
In your opinion, how could
corporate environments

00:29:31.280 --> 00:29:34.160 align:middle line:84%
and corporate working
ethics improve

00:29:34.160 --> 00:29:36.830 align:middle line:84%
to actually help
support and reduce

00:29:36.830 --> 00:29:39.950 align:middle line:84%
the work-related mental
health and stress?

00:29:39.950 --> 00:29:43.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, every human being
lives by a set of priorities,

00:29:43.130 --> 00:29:44.510 align:middle line:90%
a set of values.

00:29:44.510 --> 00:29:47.900 align:middle line:84%
And they don't go to work
for the sake of the company.

00:29:47.900 --> 00:29:50.840 align:middle line:84%
They go to work to fulfill
what's most meaningful to them,

00:29:50.840 --> 00:29:52.550 align:middle line:90%
their highest values.

00:29:52.550 --> 00:29:55.160 align:middle line:84%
So when you're hiring
somebody, in my opinion,

00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:56.480 align:middle line:90%
I think it's wise--

00:29:56.480 --> 00:29:58.340 align:middle line:90%
and I train companies on that--

00:29:58.340 --> 00:30:01.760 align:middle line:84%
to identify what's truly
their values first.

00:30:01.760 --> 00:30:03.223 align:middle line:84%
Because if every
decision they make

00:30:03.223 --> 00:30:05.390 align:middle line:84%
is based on what they believe
will give the greatest

00:30:05.390 --> 00:30:07.310 align:middle line:84%
advantage over disadvantage,
greatest reward over risk

00:30:07.310 --> 00:30:08.388 align:middle line:90%
to their highest values.

00:30:08.388 --> 00:30:10.430 align:middle line:84%
So if you don't know what
their highest value is,

00:30:10.430 --> 00:30:11.960 align:middle line:84%
you really don't
who the person is.

00:30:11.960 --> 00:30:14.692 align:middle line:84%
Because their highest value,
their life revolves around.

00:30:14.692 --> 00:30:16.400 align:middle line:84%
So first, identify
what their values are.

00:30:16.400 --> 00:30:18.740 align:middle line:84%
That takes 30 minutes on
the value determination

00:30:18.740 --> 00:30:20.745 align:middle line:90%
process on the website.

00:30:20.745 --> 00:30:22.120 align:middle line:84%
Once they've done
that, then it's

00:30:22.120 --> 00:30:24.980 align:middle line:84%
wise to go and take the job
description and the mission,

00:30:24.980 --> 00:30:27.040 align:middle line:84%
vision, and primary
objectives of the company

00:30:27.040 --> 00:30:30.190 align:middle line:84%
and to see how congruent
they are with those values.

00:30:30.190 --> 00:30:31.960 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're
about to hire somebody

00:30:31.960 --> 00:30:33.705 align:middle line:84%
and they can't see how their
job description is going

00:30:33.705 --> 00:30:35.463 align:middle line:84%
to help fulfill
their highest values,

00:30:35.463 --> 00:30:36.880 align:middle line:84%
they're not going
to be fulfilled.

00:30:36.880 --> 00:30:37.600 align:middle line:90%
They're not going to engaged.

00:30:37.600 --> 00:30:39.040 align:middle line:84%
They're not going
to be inspired.

00:30:39.040 --> 00:30:41.332 align:middle line:84%
You're going to need to
motivate them from the outside,

00:30:41.332 --> 00:30:43.360 align:middle line:84%
incentivize them with
rewards and punishments.

00:30:43.360 --> 00:30:45.208 align:middle line:84%
And they're not going
to be productive.

00:30:45.208 --> 00:30:47.500 align:middle line:84%
But if they can see how what
they're doing in their job

00:30:47.500 --> 00:30:49.150 align:middle line:84%
is fulfilling
their highest value

00:30:49.150 --> 00:30:50.983 align:middle line:84%
and they can see how
the mission the company

00:30:50.983 --> 00:30:52.720 align:middle line:84%
is helping them
fulfill their dreams,

00:30:52.720 --> 00:30:53.860 align:middle line:84%
then they're going to be
engaged because they're

00:30:53.860 --> 00:30:55.630 align:middle line:84%
going to feel like, I've got
an opportunity of a lifetime

00:30:55.630 --> 00:30:56.672 align:middle line:90%
to work for this company.

00:30:56.672 --> 00:30:58.180 align:middle line:90%
It's helping me get what I want.

00:30:58.180 --> 00:31:00.860 align:middle line:84%
Because they're going
to fulfill their values.

00:31:00.860 --> 00:31:03.310 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you hire
somebody, I recommend

00:31:03.310 --> 00:31:05.320 align:middle line:84%
hiring people and looking,
and screening them

00:31:05.320 --> 00:31:06.313 align:middle line:90%
according to values.

00:31:06.313 --> 00:31:08.230 align:middle line:84%
If they're already there
and they're maybe not

00:31:08.230 --> 00:31:10.840 align:middle line:84%
as productive and as
inspired as they could be,

00:31:10.840 --> 00:31:15.370 align:middle line:84%
then I show people, H.R.
departments and managers,

00:31:15.370 --> 00:31:17.890 align:middle line:84%
how to link their job
descriptions to their values

00:31:17.890 --> 00:31:20.080 align:middle line:84%
so they can see how what
they're doing serves them.

00:31:20.080 --> 00:31:20.770 align:middle line:90%
>> So it's there.

00:31:20.770 --> 00:31:21.770 align:middle line:90%
It just hasn't become apparent.

00:31:21.770 --> 00:31:22.840 align:middle line:84%
>> They just haven't
been aware of it.

00:31:22.840 --> 00:31:23.923 align:middle line:90%
And I show them the links.

00:31:23.923 --> 00:31:26.390 align:middle line:84%
And the skilled manager
knows how to do that.

00:31:26.390 --> 00:31:29.740 align:middle line:84%
They know how to communicate
in the values of the people,

00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:33.220 align:middle line:84%
allocate job descriptions that
match the values of the people

00:31:33.220 --> 00:31:35.708 align:middle line:84%
and/or link the job
descriptions to the values

00:31:35.708 --> 00:31:37.750 align:middle line:84%
so they're engaged, and
inspired, and productive.

00:31:37.750 --> 00:31:40.030 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise, you're going
to have to micromanage people.

00:31:40.030 --> 00:31:40.960 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
have to incentivize

00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:41.840 align:middle line:90%
them and all this other stuff.

00:31:41.840 --> 00:31:43.570 align:middle line:84%
And it weighs you
down as a company

00:31:43.570 --> 00:31:47.150 align:middle line:84%
and causes the overheads to
go up and profits to go down.

00:31:47.150 --> 00:31:49.990 align:middle line:84%
And when you're a leader, you're
living by a set of values.

00:31:49.990 --> 00:31:52.977 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to project
those values onto your people.

00:31:52.977 --> 00:31:55.060 align:middle line:84%
If you're an autocrat,
you'll project onto and not

00:31:55.060 --> 00:31:56.682 align:middle line:90%
care about the people's values.

00:31:56.682 --> 00:31:58.390 align:middle line:84%
Just like a person
going out and selling,

00:31:58.390 --> 00:32:00.473 align:middle line:84%
if they're not caring about
the customers' values,

00:32:00.473 --> 00:32:01.440 align:middle line:90%
they don't sell well.

00:32:01.440 --> 00:32:03.850 align:middle line:84%
They're looking down and
caring less about the customer

00:32:03.850 --> 00:32:05.050 align:middle line:90%
than themselves.

00:32:05.050 --> 00:32:06.640 align:middle line:84%
So the leader has
a responsibility

00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:08.530 align:middle line:84%
to communicate what
they value and what

00:32:08.530 --> 00:32:10.330 align:middle line:84%
they're wanting for
the company in terms

00:32:10.330 --> 00:32:11.950 align:middle line:90%
of the people's values.

00:32:11.950 --> 00:32:12.880 align:middle line:90%
And that's a skill.

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:14.338 align:middle line:84%
And if they don't
learn to do that,

00:32:14.338 --> 00:32:16.390 align:middle line:84%
then it becomes
autocratic and it ends up

00:32:16.390 --> 00:32:19.720 align:middle line:84%
being controlled with rules
and regulations which bog down

00:32:19.720 --> 00:32:22.600 align:middle line:90%
companies and bureaucracies.

00:32:22.600 --> 00:32:24.460 align:middle line:84%
So caring enough about
another human being

00:32:24.460 --> 00:32:26.650 align:middle line:84%
to help them fulfill
their highest values

00:32:26.650 --> 00:32:30.130 align:middle line:84%
is the secret of achievement,
customer sales, negotiation,

00:32:30.130 --> 00:32:32.230 align:middle line:84%
leadership,
management, all areas.

00:32:32.230 --> 00:32:33.370 align:middle line:90%
So I'm interested in that.

00:32:33.370 --> 00:32:35.412 align:middle line:84%
I've developed methods
for that, implemented them

00:32:35.412 --> 00:32:38.200 align:middle line:84%
into companies, and increased
the productivity and profit

00:32:38.200 --> 00:32:39.640 align:middle line:90%
line of the company--

00:32:39.640 --> 00:32:41.985 align:middle line:84%
not because they're
focused on more money.

00:32:41.985 --> 00:32:43.610 align:middle line:84%
They're focused on
caring about people.

00:32:43.610 --> 00:32:45.730 align:middle line:84%
And when people are doing
what they love, they produce.

00:32:45.730 --> 00:32:48.147 align:middle line:84%
When people can't wait to get
up in the morning and serve,

00:32:48.147 --> 00:32:49.868 align:middle line:84%
people can't wait to
get their service.

00:32:49.868 --> 00:32:51.910 align:middle line:84%
>> So what I'm hearing
there is that there's even

00:32:51.910 --> 00:32:54.460 align:middle line:84%
an appropriate way
of creating KPIs,

00:32:54.460 --> 00:32:55.990 align:middle line:84%
relevant to someone's
core value--

00:32:55.990 --> 00:32:58.787 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the KPI, if it's
not matching their values,

00:32:58.787 --> 00:33:01.120 align:middle line:84%
they're going to procrastinate,
hesitate, and frustrate.

00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:03.010 align:middle line:84%
Anything that's low
on a person's values,

00:33:03.010 --> 00:33:04.952 align:middle line:84%
they're going to need
to be reminded to do.

00:33:04.952 --> 00:33:06.160 align:middle line:90%
My highest value is teaching.

00:33:06.160 --> 00:33:07.510 align:middle line:90%
I do it every day.

00:33:07.510 --> 00:33:09.728 align:middle line:84%
My lower values are
cooking and driving.

00:33:09.728 --> 00:33:11.270 align:middle line:84%
I haven't driven in
2005 years, and I

00:33:11.270 --> 00:33:12.970 align:middle line:90%
haven't cooked since I was 24.

00:33:12.970 --> 00:33:15.640 align:middle line:84%
So the probability of me going
out and cooking and driving

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:16.802 align:middle line:90%
is like a zero.

00:33:16.802 --> 00:33:18.760 align:middle line:84%
But the probably of me
researching and teaching

00:33:18.760 --> 00:33:20.240 align:middle line:90%
is like 100%.

00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:23.230 align:middle line:84%
So if I was in a job description
that had to cook and drive,

00:33:23.230 --> 00:33:25.990 align:middle line:84%
I'd probably need punishments,
and rewards, and incentives,

00:33:25.990 --> 00:33:27.603 align:middle line:90%
and I'd probably be fired.

00:33:27.603 --> 00:33:29.020 align:middle line:84%
But you put me in
a position where

00:33:29.020 --> 00:33:31.420 align:middle line:84%
I get to research and
teach, and you don't ever

00:33:31.420 --> 00:33:33.130 align:middle line:90%
have to remind me again.

00:33:33.130 --> 00:33:34.382 align:middle line:90%
I'm in my zone.

00:33:34.382 --> 00:33:35.840 align:middle line:84%
So you've got to
make sure that you

00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:37.798 align:middle line:84%
get the right person on
the bus, as Jim Collins

00:33:37.798 --> 00:33:40.797 align:middle line:84%
says, and allocate appropriately
to their value systems.

00:33:40.797 --> 00:33:42.130 align:middle line:90%
But the key-- that's management.

00:33:42.130 --> 00:33:45.670 align:middle line:84%
As Drucker says, management
is responsible for all that.

00:33:45.670 --> 00:33:47.740 align:middle line:84%
It's not that people
are not working.

00:33:47.740 --> 00:33:49.360 align:middle line:84%
I always people
watch managers that

00:33:49.360 --> 00:33:52.090 align:middle line:84%
aren't affected hire people that
are less affected than them,

00:33:52.090 --> 00:33:55.050 align:middle line:84%
that they can control, that
they hire, that are not engaged.

00:33:55.050 --> 00:33:56.425 align:middle line:84%
And they're not
selecting wisely,

00:33:56.425 --> 00:33:58.300 align:middle line:90%
and then they blame people.

00:33:58.300 --> 00:34:01.030 align:middle line:84%
As Drucker said, it's
management's responsibility

00:34:01.030 --> 00:34:02.655 align:middle line:84%
to care enough about
people to find out

00:34:02.655 --> 00:34:05.155 align:middle line:84%
what their needs are to make
sure that their positions match

00:34:05.155 --> 00:34:06.160 align:middle line:90%
those needs.

00:34:06.160 --> 00:34:07.952 align:middle line:84%
And it may take longer
to find that person,

00:34:07.952 --> 00:34:10.077 align:middle line:84%
but once you find them,
you've got the right person

00:34:10.077 --> 00:34:11.040 align:middle line:90%
on the bus.

00:34:11.040 --> 00:34:14.440 align:middle line:84%
>> So if teaching is your
very first core value,

00:34:14.440 --> 00:34:16.170 align:middle line:90%
what is your second and third?

00:34:16.170 --> 00:34:17.409 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, mine is researching.

00:34:17.409 --> 00:34:18.790 align:middle line:90%
Love teaching is number one.

00:34:18.790 --> 00:34:20.110 align:middle line:84%
Researching and
writing is number two.

00:34:20.110 --> 00:34:22.027 align:middle line:84%
Because I research and
write every single day.

00:34:22.027 --> 00:34:23.440 align:middle line:90%
I'm always writing books.

00:34:23.440 --> 00:34:26.920 align:middle line:84%
And then, I obviously love to
travel because my life shows.

00:34:26.920 --> 00:34:29.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm at 17 million
miles of travel.

00:34:29.360 --> 00:34:32.320 align:middle line:84%
And then, probably the
next one is economics.

00:34:32.320 --> 00:34:34.820 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to get paid handsomely
to do what I love because I

00:34:34.820 --> 00:34:36.070 align:middle line:90%
wanted financial independence.

00:34:36.070 --> 00:34:37.540 align:middle line:84%
Because I didn't want
to have to do what

00:34:37.540 --> 00:34:39.159 align:middle line:84%
I did for the sake of
having to make money.

00:34:39.159 --> 00:34:41.742 align:middle line:84%
I want my money working for me
instead of me working for that.

00:34:41.742 --> 00:34:44.260 align:middle line:84%
And then, probably next is
relationships and family

00:34:44.260 --> 00:34:45.250 align:middle line:90%
dynamics.

00:34:45.250 --> 00:34:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And everybody judges
different people.

00:34:47.760 --> 00:34:50.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm always amazed how people
subordinate to other people's

00:34:50.260 --> 00:34:52.719 align:middle line:84%
expectations because they're
putting their values on you.

00:34:52.719 --> 00:34:55.060 align:middle line:84%
The key is not to subordinate
to anybody else's values,

00:34:55.060 --> 00:34:56.560 align:middle line:90%
but to live true to your own.

00:34:56.560 --> 00:34:58.540 align:middle line:84%
And I've had people
come up to me

00:34:58.540 --> 00:35:01.870 align:middle line:84%
and said, Dr. Demartini,
you hardly see your kids.

00:35:01.870 --> 00:35:02.670 align:middle line:90%
And I said, really?

00:35:02.670 --> 00:35:04.420 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, you're
a terrible father.

00:35:04.420 --> 00:35:05.530 align:middle line:90%
I said, how come?

00:35:05.530 --> 00:35:06.800 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, because
you don't see your kids.

00:35:06.800 --> 00:35:08.630 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, why would you
want a terrible father seeing

00:35:08.630 --> 00:35:09.430 align:middle line:90%
his kids?

00:35:09.430 --> 00:35:10.508 align:middle line:90%
I joke with them.

00:35:10.508 --> 00:35:12.550 align:middle line:84%
I said, because I have a
different set of values.

00:35:12.550 --> 00:35:13.990 align:middle line:84%
My kids and I have
spent a lot of time.

00:35:13.990 --> 00:35:16.075 align:middle line:84%
I was just with one in
Honolulu, and I was just

00:35:16.075 --> 00:35:18.730 align:middle line:84%
with the other one in Houston
and-- both of them in Houston,

00:35:18.730 --> 00:35:19.780 align:middle line:90%
actually-- the other two.

00:35:19.780 --> 00:35:20.860 align:middle line:90%
They're all grown up now.

00:35:20.860 --> 00:35:23.530 align:middle line:84%
But I don't have that
as my highest value.

00:35:23.530 --> 00:35:24.910 align:middle line:90%
And I'm grateful for that.

00:35:24.910 --> 00:35:25.720 align:middle line:90%
I have great kids.

00:35:25.720 --> 00:35:26.200 align:middle line:90%
I love them.

00:35:26.200 --> 00:35:27.742 align:middle line:84%
I'm inspired by
them, but they've not

00:35:27.742 --> 00:35:29.500 align:middle line:90%
been always my highest value.

00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:31.580 align:middle line:84%
And they don't have me
as their highest value.

00:35:31.580 --> 00:35:34.180 align:middle line:84%
So you've just got to be honest
with who you are and not try

00:35:34.180 --> 00:35:35.997 align:middle line:90%
to set goals that aren't you.

00:35:35.997 --> 00:35:38.080 align:middle line:84%
If you set a goal that's
not matching your values,

00:35:38.080 --> 00:35:39.830 align:middle line:84%
you're going to end up with
the ABCDs of negativity.

00:35:39.830 --> 00:35:41.163 align:middle line:90%
You're going to feel depressed.

00:35:41.163 --> 00:35:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And you're going
to get a feedback

00:35:42.580 --> 00:35:44.260 align:middle line:84%
to say you're not
being authentic.

00:35:44.260 --> 00:35:46.978 align:middle line:84%
I'd rather be able to say I
love me for who I am, and go

00:35:46.978 --> 00:35:48.520 align:middle line:84%
and do what I love,
and inspire them.

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Because then, I teach my
kids to go and be authentic.

00:35:51.290 --> 00:35:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And all three my kids have their
missions today because of it.

00:35:54.260 --> 00:35:55.190 align:middle line:84%
They know what
they're wanting to do.

00:35:55.190 --> 00:35:56.148 align:middle line:90%
They're going after it.

00:35:56.148 --> 00:35:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And they've been
succeeding at it.

00:35:58.250 --> 00:36:01.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Does exercise, sit
anywhere on a value for you?

00:36:01.210 --> 00:36:02.890 align:middle line:90%
>> I do.

00:36:02.890 --> 00:36:06.070 align:middle line:84%
Instead of "Ab Magazine,"
I'm on "Blab Magazine."

00:36:06.070 --> 00:36:08.770 align:middle line:84%
I got ripples on the side
of my masseter muscle

00:36:08.770 --> 00:36:10.000 align:middle line:90%
because I speak so much.

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:11.033 align:middle line:90%
No, I work out.

00:36:11.033 --> 00:36:13.200 align:middle line:84%
And I have wires to my jaw
to all the other muscles.

00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:14.992 align:middle line:84%
So whenever I speak,
it's using my muscles.

00:36:14.992 --> 00:36:16.090 align:middle line:90%
>> Just everything.

00:36:16.090 --> 00:36:19.930 align:middle line:84%
>> I do push-ups, and sit-ups,
and stretch, and some yoga,

00:36:19.930 --> 00:36:23.590 align:middle line:84%
and some swimming, and then
some surfing occasionally.

00:36:23.590 --> 00:36:26.290 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not this gym fanatic.

00:36:26.290 --> 00:36:27.705 align:middle line:90%
I workout and I'm doing good.

00:36:27.705 --> 00:36:29.080 align:middle line:84%
I'm 61 and I'm
doing pretty good.

00:36:29.080 --> 00:36:31.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow, 61.

00:36:31.600 --> 00:36:32.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh my goodness.

00:36:32.920 --> 00:36:33.920 align:middle line:90%
You look amazing for 61.

00:36:33.920 --> 00:36:35.380 align:middle line:90%
>> I've been blessed.

00:36:35.380 --> 00:36:37.570 align:middle line:84%
I had a young
woman come up to me

00:36:37.570 --> 00:36:39.820 align:middle line:84%
one time in a
Cheesecake Factory.

00:36:39.820 --> 00:36:42.700 align:middle line:84%
I was in kind of a darkened
Cheesecake Factory restaurant

00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:44.820 align:middle line:84%
and I was slurping
some soup really quick.

00:36:44.820 --> 00:36:47.037 align:middle line:84%
And this girl came up
to me and she said, sir,

00:36:47.037 --> 00:36:49.120 align:middle line:84%
would you like to join me
and this other lady over

00:36:49.120 --> 00:36:50.140 align:middle line:90%
at the table?

00:36:50.140 --> 00:36:50.973 align:middle line:90%
I looked over there.

00:36:50.973 --> 00:36:53.290 align:middle line:84%
There was another girl over
there about half my age.

00:36:53.290 --> 00:36:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
this is ridiculous.

00:36:55.360 --> 00:36:56.860 align:middle line:84%
And I said, do you
mind if I ask you

00:36:56.860 --> 00:36:57.710 align:middle line:90%
what made you come over here?

00:36:57.710 --> 00:36:59.335 align:middle line:84%
She says, well, you
looked interesting.

00:36:59.335 --> 00:37:00.800 align:middle line:90%
You looked successful.

00:37:00.800 --> 00:37:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And we thought it would
be entertaining to have

00:37:03.280 --> 00:37:04.210 align:middle line:90%
you come and join us.

00:37:04.210 --> 00:37:05.470 align:middle line:84%
I said, well,
thank you for that.

00:37:05.470 --> 00:37:07.030 align:middle line:84%
I said, do you mind if I
ask you another question?

00:37:07.030 --> 00:37:07.540 align:middle line:90%
She says, no.

00:37:07.540 --> 00:37:09.160 align:middle line:84%
I said, how old
do you think I am?

00:37:09.160 --> 00:37:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, I
thought you were maybe

00:37:10.540 --> 00:37:11.980 align:middle line:90%
mid-40s or something like that.

00:37:11.980 --> 00:37:14.362 align:middle line:84%
And I said, if I told you
I was more the 60 mark,

00:37:14.362 --> 00:37:15.820 align:middle line:84%
would you still
want me over there?

00:37:15.820 --> 00:37:18.630 align:middle line:90%
She says, well, if you're busy--

00:37:18.630 --> 00:37:19.906 align:middle line:90%
>> Gone.

00:37:19.906 --> 00:37:21.220 align:middle line:90%
>> I thought that was so funny.

00:37:21.220 --> 00:37:22.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Very funny.

00:37:22.020 --> 00:37:24.680 align:middle line:84%
>> But she was in
a dark environment.

00:37:24.680 --> 00:37:27.530 align:middle line:84%
It helped me look
a little younger.

00:37:27.530 --> 00:37:31.390 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so I have to ask
because of my love of food

00:37:31.390 --> 00:37:33.640 align:middle line:84%
and nutrition--
what's your diet?

00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.290 align:middle line:90%
>> My diet?

00:37:35.290 --> 00:37:36.880 align:middle line:84%
Well, first of all,
I'm a water freak.

00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:38.830 align:middle line:84%
I don't drink
anything but water--

00:37:38.830 --> 00:37:41.960 align:middle line:84%
so no sweets, no
coffees, no teas.

00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:43.960 align:middle line:84%
I've had three cups of
coffee in my entire life.

00:37:43.960 --> 00:37:45.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't drink
anything but water.

00:37:45.190 --> 00:37:46.023 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:37:46.023 --> 00:37:48.660 align:middle line:84%
>> And is there a type
of quality of water?

00:37:48.660 --> 00:37:50.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I've investigated
bottled waters,

00:37:50.410 --> 00:37:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and not all bottled waters
are really that great.

00:37:52.060 --> 00:37:53.650 align:middle line:84%
So I try to get the
best water I can.

00:37:53.650 --> 00:37:56.950 align:middle line:84%
And filtered water is probably
one of the better ones today--

00:37:56.950 --> 00:37:58.760 align:middle line:90%
some bottled water.

00:37:58.760 --> 00:38:01.450 align:middle line:84%
But in the morning, I have
fresh fruit-- usually grapes--

00:38:01.450 --> 00:38:03.280 align:middle line:84%
but usually fresh
fruit-- mango, something

00:38:03.280 --> 00:38:08.170 align:middle line:84%
like that, yogurt or cottage
cheese, and multigrain toast.

00:38:08.170 --> 00:38:09.490 align:middle line:90%
That's a typical breakfast.

00:38:09.490 --> 00:38:12.730 align:middle line:84%
At lunch, I'll usually have
a soup, a salad, a sandwich,

00:38:12.730 --> 00:38:15.150 align:middle line:90%
sushi, or salmon.

00:38:15.150 --> 00:38:18.130 align:middle line:84%
And most of time, it's
a sandwich or a salad.

00:38:18.130 --> 00:38:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And at dinner, I usually have
some salmon or some fish,

00:38:20.860 --> 00:38:23.330 align:middle line:84%
some carrots, some spinach,
and some multigrain bread.

00:38:23.330 --> 00:38:24.130 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:38:24.130 --> 00:38:25.248 align:middle line:90%
I'm a really simple guy.

00:38:25.248 --> 00:38:27.790 align:middle line:84%
And people always want to take
me to these fancy restaurants.

00:38:27.790 --> 00:38:30.408 align:middle line:84%
I said, can I get
a bowl of soup?

00:38:30.408 --> 00:38:32.950 align:middle line:84%
And they go, we're taking you
to the best restaurant in town.

00:38:32.950 --> 00:38:35.090 align:middle line:84%
I go, I'd like a bowl
of soup, thank you.

00:38:35.090 --> 00:38:37.480 align:middle line:84%
And I don't want all the
creamy, cheesy stuff.

00:38:37.480 --> 00:38:39.608 align:middle line:84%
I don't like oily, boiling,
limping, wimpy foods.

00:38:39.608 --> 00:38:41.650 align:middle line:84%
I like something that has
substance and something

00:38:41.650 --> 00:38:42.450 align:middle line:90%
that's--

00:38:42.450 --> 00:38:44.267 align:middle line:84%
I learned a long time
ago from Paul Bragg.

00:38:44.267 --> 00:38:45.100 align:middle line:90%
I don't live to eat.

00:38:45.100 --> 00:38:45.900 align:middle line:90%
I eat to live.

00:38:45.900 --> 00:38:48.442 align:middle line:84%
So I don't want to put something
in my body that's not really

00:38:48.442 --> 00:38:50.560 align:middle line:84%
going to help me perform
and help me accomplish

00:38:50.560 --> 00:38:51.660 align:middle line:90%
what I want to accomplish.

00:38:51.660 --> 00:38:53.380 align:middle line:84%
Because it's too important--
my life's too important.

00:38:53.380 --> 00:38:54.910 align:middle line:84%
>> So do you choose
organically for that--

00:38:54.910 --> 00:38:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>> If I can.

00:38:55.630 --> 00:38:57.130 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, I'm
traveling counseling.

00:38:57.130 --> 00:38:59.830 align:middle line:84%
So I don't just go,
organic in first class,

00:38:59.830 --> 00:39:01.690 align:middle line:90%
thank you-- organic.

00:39:01.690 --> 00:39:02.490 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:39:02.490 --> 00:39:03.490 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:39:03.490 --> 00:39:04.833 align:middle line:90%
>> --I try to do the best I can.

00:39:04.833 --> 00:39:06.250 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm in
certain locations,

00:39:06.250 --> 00:39:07.300 align:middle line:90%
I can get really quality food.

00:39:07.300 --> 00:39:08.390 align:middle line:90%
In some areas, I can't.

00:39:08.390 --> 00:39:11.650 align:middle line:84%
So I don't sit there and
ram my head about it.

00:39:11.650 --> 00:39:12.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm grateful for it.

00:39:12.820 --> 00:39:15.100 align:middle line:84%
I realize that we can get
so neurotic about what

00:39:15.100 --> 00:39:17.740 align:middle line:84%
we eat that we can
make the anxiety

00:39:17.740 --> 00:39:19.115 align:middle line:84%
and cause the
problems from that.

00:39:19.115 --> 00:39:21.448 align:middle line:84%
So if I'm in an environment
where I can get the greatest

00:39:21.448 --> 00:39:22.460 align:middle line:90%
food, I get it.

00:39:22.460 --> 00:39:25.510 align:middle line:84%
If I'm not, I'd be grateful for
what I get, and I eat wisely.

00:39:25.510 --> 00:39:27.160 align:middle line:84%
And I can always
find those things,

00:39:27.160 --> 00:39:28.080 align:middle line:90%
wherever I go around the world.

00:39:28.080 --> 00:39:28.880 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:33.370 align:middle line:84%
Two last questions-- we've taken
the stigma out of mental health

00:39:33.370 --> 00:39:34.490 align:middle line:90%
as being an illness.

00:39:34.490 --> 00:39:38.050 align:middle line:84%
So if we don't, here today,
call mental health an illness,

00:39:38.050 --> 00:39:39.700 align:middle line:90%
what do we call it?

00:39:39.700 --> 00:39:42.580 align:middle line:84%
>> I call mental illness as a
feedback mechanism to help us

00:39:42.580 --> 00:39:46.480 align:middle line:84%
live more authentically and
guide us to live by our highest

00:39:46.480 --> 00:39:47.350 align:middle line:90%
values.

00:39:47.350 --> 00:39:50.680 align:middle line:84%
Because when people do, their
entire psychology changes.

00:39:50.680 --> 00:39:52.660 align:middle line:84%
When people start to
prioritize their life--

00:39:52.660 --> 00:39:56.350 align:middle line:84%
I was speaking in Dallas, Texas
at the Anatole for Mary Kay

00:39:56.350 --> 00:39:57.550 align:middle line:90%
Cosmetics.

00:39:57.550 --> 00:39:59.380 align:middle line:84%
And Mary Kay Ash
was an amazing lady.

00:39:59.380 --> 00:40:01.320 align:middle line:90%
She's impacted a lot of women.

00:40:01.320 --> 00:40:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And I walked up to Mary Kay
after I spoke, and I said,

00:40:03.700 --> 00:40:06.310 align:middle line:84%
what advice can you give a
young, aspiring speaker that's

00:40:06.310 --> 00:40:08.858 align:middle line:90%
traveling the world speaking?

00:40:08.858 --> 00:40:10.150 align:middle line:90%
She had her hair all like this.

00:40:10.150 --> 00:40:13.090 align:middle line:84%
She said, every day, write
down the six or seven highest

00:40:13.090 --> 00:40:15.190 align:middle line:84%
priority actions
that you can do today

00:40:15.190 --> 00:40:17.670 align:middle line:84%
that can help you fulfill your
dreams, and go and do them.

00:40:17.670 --> 00:40:19.920 align:middle line:84%
They're just daily actions,
not projects-- daily

00:40:19.920 --> 00:40:21.780 align:middle line:90%
acts you can get done that day.

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:22.812 align:middle line:90%
And go get them done.

00:40:22.812 --> 00:40:24.770 align:middle line:84%
And then reward yourself
at the end of the day.

00:40:24.770 --> 00:40:27.970 align:middle line:84%
And when you prioritize your
life, you live by the ABCs,

00:40:27.970 --> 00:40:28.912 align:middle line:90%
you grow and so forth.

00:40:28.912 --> 00:40:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And you're growing
accomplishments.

00:40:30.370 --> 00:40:33.820 align:middle line:84%
And little, baby steps build
momentum into big dreams.

00:40:33.820 --> 00:40:36.070 align:middle line:84%
And if you set big goals
that are overwhelming,

00:40:36.070 --> 00:40:39.040 align:middle line:84%
and they're not yours,
and they're expectations,

00:40:39.040 --> 00:40:42.460 align:middle line:84%
and they're subordinate from
other people's projections,

00:40:42.460 --> 00:40:43.540 align:middle line:90%
you beat yourself up.

00:40:43.540 --> 00:40:46.510 align:middle line:84%
So you when you do that,
and you strategize your life

00:40:46.510 --> 00:40:50.890 align:middle line:84%
effectively, you're grateful,
you feel love for life,

00:40:50.890 --> 00:40:52.105 align:middle line:90%
and you achieve.

00:40:52.105 --> 00:40:54.480 align:middle line:84%
So I always say that anything
you can't say thank you for

00:40:54.480 --> 00:40:55.480 align:middle line:90%
is baggage.

00:40:55.480 --> 00:40:58.270 align:middle line:84%
And mental health is trying
to get you to live that way.

00:40:58.270 --> 00:41:00.860 align:middle line:84%
Mental health is attempting
to get you authentically.

00:41:00.860 --> 00:41:02.680 align:middle line:84%
And you keep holding
onto fantasies.

00:41:02.680 --> 00:41:04.888 align:middle line:84%
You keep subordinating to
other people's expectation.

00:41:04.888 --> 00:41:06.888 align:middle line:84%
We're not here to live
in the shadows of anyone.

00:41:06.888 --> 00:41:08.882 align:middle line:84%
We're here to stand on
the shoulders of giants.

00:41:08.882 --> 00:41:10.670 align:middle line:90%
>> I love it.

00:41:10.670 --> 00:41:14.470 align:middle line:84%
So that's a beautiful
segue to my last question.

00:41:14.470 --> 00:41:16.510 align:middle line:84%
We're a great believer
at Healthy ME Summits

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:19.780 align:middle line:84%
on the "I am" statement,
and that neuroscience

00:41:19.780 --> 00:41:22.780 align:middle line:84%
has done a wonderful job
at validating finally

00:41:22.780 --> 00:41:25.390 align:middle line:84%
what philosophers of all
time have always said--

00:41:25.390 --> 00:41:27.270 align:middle line:90%
we are what we think.

00:41:27.270 --> 00:41:29.830 align:middle line:84%
What is your "I am"
statement every morning?

00:41:29.830 --> 00:41:32.890 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it was Descartes,
the French philosopher

00:41:32.890 --> 00:41:37.480 align:middle line:84%
and mathematician, who basically
said, I think, therefore I am.

00:41:37.480 --> 00:41:40.000 align:middle line:90%


00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:42.250 align:middle line:90%
My statement, my affirmation--

00:41:42.250 --> 00:41:44.410 align:middle line:84%
my first affirmation
that I ever got

00:41:44.410 --> 00:41:46.900 align:middle line:84%
was from my fourth
grade teacher.

00:41:46.900 --> 00:41:48.190 align:middle line:90%
I am quiet.

00:41:48.190 --> 00:41:49.180 align:middle line:90%
I sit in my chair.

00:41:49.180 --> 00:41:51.440 align:middle line:90%
And I do my homework.

00:41:51.440 --> 00:41:52.960 align:middle line:90%
And that worked, actually.

00:41:52.960 --> 00:41:54.850 align:middle line:90%
I stopped talking.

00:41:54.850 --> 00:41:56.470 align:middle line:84%
My second affirmation
was given to me

00:41:56.470 --> 00:42:00.400 align:middle line:84%
by Paul Bragg when I
had learning problems.

00:42:00.400 --> 00:42:04.240 align:middle line:84%
He said, to overcome, say, I am
a genius and I apply my wisdom.

00:42:04.240 --> 00:42:05.680 align:middle line:84%
And that had an
impact on my life.

00:42:05.680 --> 00:42:08.330 align:middle line:84%
And I still say that every
single day of my life.

00:42:08.330 --> 00:42:11.950 align:middle line:84%
But I would say
that I'm just me.

00:42:11.950 --> 00:42:12.850 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:42:12.850 --> 00:42:14.200 align:middle line:90%
I'm just me.

00:42:14.200 --> 00:42:16.480 align:middle line:84%
People want to be something
other than who they are.

00:42:16.480 --> 00:42:18.190 align:middle line:84%
I was asked by "Vogue
Magazine" one time,

00:42:18.190 --> 00:42:19.660 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Demartini, if
there's anybody

00:42:19.660 --> 00:42:21.100 align:middle line:84%
in the world you could be
in the world, who could

00:42:21.100 --> 00:42:21.900 align:middle line:90%
you want to be?

00:42:21.900 --> 00:42:23.170 align:middle line:90%
I go, me.

00:42:23.170 --> 00:42:24.230 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't want to
be anybody but me.

00:42:24.230 --> 00:42:25.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Everyone else is taken.

00:42:25.120 --> 00:42:25.530 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:42:25.530 --> 00:42:27.070 align:middle line:84%
Everybody else was
taken and I can't

00:42:27.070 --> 00:42:28.903 align:middle line:84%
think of anybody else
I'd rather be than me.

00:42:28.903 --> 00:42:31.450 align:middle line:84%
So I love myself,
and that's great.

00:42:31.450 --> 00:42:33.250 align:middle line:84%
So many people have
difficulty doing that.

00:42:33.250 --> 00:42:35.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Dr. Demartini, thank you
so much for joining us--

00:42:35.780 --> 00:42:36.850 align:middle line:84%
it's been an absolute
pleasure-- for--

00:42:36.850 --> 00:42:37.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:42:37.150 --> 00:42:38.525 align:middle line:84%
>> --your wisdom,
your knowledge,

00:42:38.525 --> 00:42:39.680 align:middle line:90%
and your time and energy.

00:42:39.680 --> 00:42:41.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you for bringing
this message to the world.

00:42:41.630 --> 00:42:42.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:42:42.430 --> 00:42:44.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:42:44.610 --> 00:42:47.000 align:middle line:90%